title: mary's quick stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, pepper and parsley; simmer until onion and pepper are clear.
Add tomato sauce, carrots, potatoes and salt.
Simmer 10 more minutes.

title: snickers brownies
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir into sugar mixture.
Fold in chopped Snickers bars.
Spoon into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch Teflon pan.
Sprinkle with chopped Hershey bars.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: barbecue rice
directions: Cook rice according to package. Melt butter in a skillet. Saute celery and onions until tender. Combine all ingredients into large oven-safe pan. Stir well. Add liquid smoke. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour an 8-inch square pan. Melt butter and bittersweet chocolate chips in small, heavy saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat; cool.
Beat the eggs, sugar and vanilla in large bowl until light.
Beat in chocolate mixture.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt until just blended.
Spread 3/4 of the batter into prepared pan; sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread preserves over almonds.
Carefully spoon remaining batter over preserves, smoothing top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or just until top feels firm.
Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Let stand a few minutes, until chips melt, then spread evenly over brownies.
Cool completely.
Makes 16 servings.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: cranberry meatball appetizer
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine rest of ingredients in medium bowl.
Shape meat mixture into small balls and place in large baking pan.
Pour sauce mixture over meatballs, evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nutty cherry squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugar, nuts, soda and melted margarine in a large bowl. Work mixture into crumbs and reserve 1 1/2 cups for topping. Press remaining crumbs into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 minutes. Remove from oven and spoon pie filling over hot crust. Sprinkle with marshmallows and top with remaining crumbs. Return to oven and bake 30 to 35 minutes until top crumbs are lightly browned. Remove from oven and cool. Cut into squares to serve.

title: french chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and put in roasting pan.
Cover with dressing.
Sprinkle soup over top and refrigerate overnight. Bake, covered, 2 hours at 300°, basting often.

title: beef dip
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Drain fat from meat.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheeses.
Stir over heat until cheeses are well combined.
Makes 3 cups.

title: gloria's crazy crust pie
directions: *If using apple pie filling, combine pie filling with cinnamon.

title: "nine to five" meat loaf
directions: Mix all and place in metal bread pan.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 24 hours.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake on lowest shelf of oven for 20 minutes.
Remove and place under broiler for 5 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4.

title: mary's pudding
directions: Add yolks of 2 beaten eggs after milk has thickened. Put in pudding dish and let cool.

title: basic corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: three layer "sawdust" salad
directions: Mix lemon and
orange Jell-O in boiling water, then add cold water.
Add
pineapple,
marshmallows
and bananas.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex and let congeal.

title: pork chops and vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet over medium heat; add oil, brown both sides of chops.
Grease 13 x 9-inch dish.
Toss in all ingredients.
Arrange chops on top.
Cover dish with foil and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: stack-a-dinner
directions: In skillet, brown meat with onion; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, next 3 ingredients, water and salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling, stirring often.
Cook rice and prepare peas following package directions.
On individual serving plates, layer rice, peas, meat mixture, then cheese.
Trim with olives.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a glass round baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Then crush Ritz crackers and add melted margarine.
Mix margarine and crackers together and pour over casserole.
Bake another 20 minutes.
Do not cover when baking or reheating.
Good as a side dish or dessert.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Heat sugar and milk in a 1 quart saucepan over medium heat. Blend egg yolks and cornstarch.
Add small amount of hot milk to yolk mixture.
Mix well and return to the hot milk.
Boil until thick, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla, coconut and salt.
Stir until butter melts.
Cool.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Whip and sweeten cream; spread over pie.
Garnish with grated coconut.
Serve chilled.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: In a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender, drain. Stir in all remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 15-20 minutes. Top each serving with a dollop
(about 1 tsp.) of sour cream and sprinkle with cheese. Serve with corn chips on the side. Makes 12 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans in salted water; drain.
Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with 1/2 can onions and pimento.
Bake 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix thoroughly cheese, butter, hot pepper sauce, salt, paprika and flour.
Form portion of dough around well-drained olive.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Can be made ahead and frozen and cooked just before serving.

title: mexican buffet
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain off fat.
Place in heavy pot and add tomato sauce, enchilada sauce, green chili salsa, chili beans and garlic salt.
Cook slowly for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Place Fritos on plate with meat mixture over them. Add grated cheese, diced tomatoes, onions, shredded lettuce and sour cream.

title: angel delight
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and juice.
Chill until thick.
Fold Cool Whip into chilled mixture.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with half of angel food cake (torn).
Cover with half of mixture. Repeat layers and cover with Cool Whip.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: tomato salad(insalata di pomodori)
directions: Cut tomatoes into wedges
and
arrange
in
large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and gently toss.
Prepare at least 2 hours before serving.
Refrigerate.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: black forest chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, chocolate, eagle brand milk, eggs, cornstarch and almond extract until smooth.
Pour into springform pan, bake 55 minutes to an hour or until center is set.
Chill. Top with cherry pie filling and cool whip before serving.

title: puppy chow(rachel's kind)
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients.
Pour over cereal and stir lightly until coated.
Put powdered sugar (1/2 to 3/4 pound box) in brown bag.
Shake until cereal is coated.

title: marinated beef and broccoli supper
directions: In 10-inch (25 cm.) skillet, melt butter until sizzling.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until crispy tender (5 to 6 minutes).
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, stir together remaining ingredients, except steak, tomatoes and rice.
Add sirloin strips; let stand 5 minutes.
Add sirloin and marinade to vegetable mixture.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until meat is browned (6 to 8 minutes).
Stir in tomatoes.
Cover; let stand 2 minutes or until heated through. Serve meat and vegetables with juices over rice.

title: chocolate chess cake
directions: Beat until smooth and pour over chocolate layer.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: orange delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend in blender for 30 seconds.

title: rosie's pureed vegetable soup
directions: Combine the 5 cups vegetables and stock in large pot.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes over a medium heat until the vegetables are tender. Spoon the mixture into a blender or food processor.
Add the miso or cornstarch and cream cheese; puree until smooth.
(You may want to divide vegetables so as not to overfill the blender or food processor.)
Return the mixture to the pot.
Stir in the remaining ingredients, except the peas, and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the peas and simmer another 5 minutes.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Beat the egg well and mix with melted shortening and milk.
Mix with dry ingredients to form a dough.
Cook, closely covered, in boiling water, broth or gravy for 18 minutes, dropping the dumplings from a spoon into the boiling liquid.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Combine melted butter, egg and cake mix.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine softened cream cheese with 2 beaten eggs, brown sugar, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° until cake is golden brown on top, approximately 45 minutes.
Cut into small squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate chip bars *
directions: Beat the eggs until thick and foamy.
Gradually add the sugar and continue beating until very well blended.
Add the oil and vanilla; mix well.
Add the flour, baking powder and salt which have been sifted together.
Fold in the pecans and chocolate pieces.
Spread in a greased 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 1 x 3-inch bars. Yield: 30 bars.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Gradually mix in flour and nuts. Shape dough into small crescents or balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.
While cookies are still warm, dust or roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chad's chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Heat and stir well until all ingredients have blended together.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
May also be prepared and served in a crock-pot.

title: super chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate
in
hot water;
set aside to cool.
Mix yeast and
warm
water.
Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add egg yolks,
one
at
a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla, chocolate and yeast mixture.
Sift
flour with salt and cocoa. Stir soda into
buttermilk.
Add alternately flour and buttermilk, beating well after
each
addition.
Fold in egg whites. Bake in 4 layers at
350° for 35 minutes.
Put filling between layers and frost.

title: salsa caliente
directions: Combine the grilled tomatoes with peppers and garlic; blend to a puree.
Cook onion in oil until opaque.
Add tomato mixture and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until no longer raw tasting.
The mixture should be smooth.
Add chicken stock if too thick.
Season with salt to taste.
This sauce freezes well.

title: refreshing light pie
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add sugar and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Beat Pet milk with electric mixer until frothy.
Add gelatin and beat until stiff (peaks form).
Pour into crust. Chill 4 hours or until firm.

title: suzie bodenhamer's coconut pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add to milk.
Add egg yolks and salt.
Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add as much frozen coconut as desired.
(I use 1 small package for each pie.)
Top with Cool Whip or any whipped topping.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Roll out and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: zucchini and rice delight
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger and drain. Add onions and peppers. Cover. Stir. In 5 minutes, add garlic salt, zucchini, stewed tomatoes and lemon juice. Cover and simmer. Bring water to boil, add rice and cover. Shut off stove. Serve skillet mixture over rice.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Serve with vegetables (cucumbers, carrots, cauliflower, etc.).

title: party sandwich loaf
directions: Seal jars; okra should be ready after 2 weeks.
Serve ice cold.
Makes 4 or 5 pints.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well and mix together.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Let cool and then pour over vegetables.
Chill for 24 hours and serve.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 2 cups of grated Cheddar cheese and 2 cups corn flakes.
Melt oleo and lightly pour on corn flakes.
Bake
1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: farm-stand ratatouille
directions: In a 4 or 5-quart Dutch oven, cook onions and garlic in hot olive oil or cooking oil for 3 to 4 minutes, or until onions are tender but not brown.

Stir in eggplant, zucchini, tomatoes, summer squash, green pepper, basil, oregano, salt and pepper. Cover; cook for about 20 minutes, until vegetables are tender. Cook, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes more, or until liquid is slightly reduced.
Remove from heat.
Allow to cool slightly.
If desired, stir in Mozzarella cheese.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken with red wine
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bag.
Shake chicken in the bag.
Put in dish; pour melted butter over it.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 350°. Add onions, olives and wine.
Cover and bake for 1/2 hour. Remove cover; cook 15 minutes to brown.

title: applesauce date cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix half of flour mixture with nuts and dates, coating well.
Mix rest of other ingredients together.
Blend in flour mixtures.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: date nut loaf cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil and mix well.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Place in a greased floured loaf pan.
Bake in slow oven 2 hours at 300°.
Start cake in a cold oven.
Makes one (3-pound) loaf.

title: rhubarb meringue pie
directions: Bake crust 10 minutes at 400°.
Microwave rhubarb, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in covered dish for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring once (High).
Make meringue with egg whites, 6 tablespoons of sugar and vanilla.

title: sangria
directions: In a large pitcher, stir together the wine, juice, sugar, peaches, oranges and lemon.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: pizza roll-up
directions: Thaw bread dough and roll out to 12x9 inch rectangle.
Spread with tomato paste.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Seal and place on greased baking sheet.
Seam side down.
Brush with water and sprinkle with a little salt.
Let rise until almost double.
Make shallow slashes across top.
Bake 375 about 30 minutes or until done.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown and season hamburger, then place hamburger in a casserole dish.
Add macaroni, potatoes, vegetable soup, tomato sauce and cheese.
Mix ingredients together; bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in eggs and corn, mixing well.
Fry in oil.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls. Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Good served with maple syrup.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: grilled margarita chicken(serves 8)
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring until blended.
Pour olive oil mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill, covered, over medium hot coals (350° to 400°) for 10 minutes on each side, or until chicken is done, turning and basting occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Set aside.
Add salt and spices to sifted flour, reserving 4 tablespoons for dredging of raisins and nuts. Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce to the creamed shortening and sugar mixture.
Dredge nut meats and raisins with 4 tablespoons of flour.
Hand stir into cake batter. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. When cake tester is clean, remove.
Let rest 10 to 15 minutes. Turn out on rack to cool.
When cool, wrap in tinfoil to keep moist.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash kraut in warm water unless all salt is removed.
Squeeze out water.
Add other vegetables.
Mix sugar, oil and vinegar. Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Add 1 teaspoon celery seed and pour over mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: orange pie
directions: Prick pie crust and bake.
Put grated rind and juice of oranges and lemon, cold water and 1 1/2 cups sugar into double boiler.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat, eggs, onions, salt, pepper, and sage; mix well.
Form in a loaf and place in greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
6 servings.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Dip chicken breast in egg and bread crumbs.
Brown in oil. Remove and place in casserole dish.
Saute tomato, onion, garlic and peppers in 2 tablespoons olive oil (5 minutes until tender). Place on top of chicken breasts.
Pour on raw rice and cover all with chicken broth.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Serve with stemmed broccoli or top with peas.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400° with pie plate and butter in the oven. Remove pan when butter is melted.
In bowl beat eggs well; add milk and beat in.
Add flour and beat in.
Pour in hot pie plate. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Recipe makes 1 large pancake or 2 small.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar then eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add alternately the flour and sour cream to the mixture, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
In a small bowl, mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
In tube pan put half of the batter and half of sugar/cinnamon mixture. Add remaining batter and rest of sugar/cinnamon on top.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco until fine crumbs.
Add water; press into ball.
Roll out on floured surface.
Makes 1 (12-inch) crust.

title: lowfat chicken and rice primavera
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Pour the uncooked rice in the bottom of a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Layer the chicken over the rice.
Add the drained tomatoes and vegetables. Combine the liquid from the tomatoes and vegetables with enough chicken broth to make 2 1/2 cups of liquid.
Add this to the mushroom soup and heat. Pour this mixture over the vegetables.
Sprinkle the cheese over top of the casserole.
Bake for about 35 minutes.
Makes 10 generous servings.
Less than 4 grams of fat per serving.

title: taco dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread refried beans evenly on bottom of pan.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over the beans.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: wine cake
directions: Bake in greased angel food cake tin at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes, then remove.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Put pork roast in crock-pot.
Add 1/2 cup water. Cook on low all day.
Take out; let drain.
Let cool enough to separate lean meat from fat. Put back into crock-pot.
Add barbecue sauce as desired.
Cook on low for about 1 hour.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and egg.
Add molasses, flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine until smooth.
Shape dough into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry coconut squares
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, margarine and powdered sugar for the pastry.
Press mixture into a greased and floured 8-inch square pan (I use a 7 x 11-inch pan).
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: amish cheese cake
directions: Mix the crumbs, sugar (1 1/2 tablespoons) and melted butter together.
Press into a buttered spring-form pan.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in bottom of pan; spread soup over it. Sprinkle on cheese.
Sprinkle on stuffing and then pour over melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: english scones
directions: Mix cream of tartar, baking soda and flour; rub in butter with pastry fork.
Add sugar and fruit.
Mix egg (1) and milk and add to flour mixture until spongy.
Form into 16 scones and brush with remaining egg.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Set aside.
Slice potatoes and onions and place in casserole dish.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Uncover the last 10 minutes.

title: bean pie, light as a breeze
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
If crust is frozen, set it out to thaw while making filling.
In a mixing bowl, beat together margarine, buttermilk and sugar.
Add flour and cinnamon; blend well.
Add egg and egg whites and beat well.
Rinse, drain and mash beans. Add beans, milk and vanilla to flour mixture; beat well.
Spoon filling into thawed crust.
Place pie on baking sheet and bake 5 minutes.
Lower temperature to 325° and bake an additional 45 to 50 minutes longer, until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: chicken stir-fry(serves 4)
directions: In shallow glass bowl, combine orange juice and cornstarch. Mix well.
Stir in chicken.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Drain chicken. Discard juice.
In small bowl, combine broth and soy sauce.
Set aside.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Use half of the lettuce; sprinkle with sugar and pepper.
Layer eggs on top.
Sprinkle with salt.
Layer peas, some lettuce, bacon, more lettuce, then chestnuts.
Layer rest of lettuce, then cheese. Put mayonnaise on top to edge of bowl.
Refrigerate for 12 to 14 hours.
Garnish with onions.
May toss, if desired.

title: italian style chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: peach crinkle
directions: Place peaches in medium size baking dish. Add lemon rind, if used. Crumble pie crust and sugar together, mixing well.
Dust onto peaches and dot liberally with butter or oleo.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm with cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Beat egg.
Mix broccoli, soup, egg, onion, butter, cheese and seasonings.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Soak chicken in egg, then coat with bread crumbs and fry in oil until brown.
Place in baking dish.
Cover chicken with sliced mushrooms, then Muenster cheese.
Pour broth over until chicken is half covered.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 45 minutes, last 10 minutes, remove foil until golden brown.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain juice from all fruits.
Place in 8-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar and curry powder and sprinkle over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Let set at least 30 minutes, longer is better and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glazed peanuts
directions: Combine peanuts, water and sugar in saucepan; stir over medium heat until all liquid evaporates.
Pour on cookie sheet and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir and return to oven for 15 minutes.
Stir again and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let cool and store.
Makes approximately 6 cups.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
together.
Use 2 to 3 tablespoons per coffee mug with very hot water.

title: spiced wine
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients except wine; let simmer 45 minutes.
Add wine.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Let spices settle to bottom.
Serve hot in mug.
May garnish with wedge of lemon or orange.

title: chicken kelly ii
directions: Marinate chicken in eggs for 2 hours in the refrigerator. Combine bread crumbs, salt, parsley and garlic powder in plastic bag.
Shake chicken in bread crumbs and brown in oil.
Drain and place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with a layer of mushrooms, layer of cheese and top with chicken broth.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms; slice stems and caps.
Saute mushrooms until brown.
Line shallow 10-inch casserole with cooked spinach, which has been seasoned with the salt, chopped onion and melted butter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of grated Cheddar cheese.
Arrange the sauteed mushrooms over the spinach.
Season with garlic salt (to taste).
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.
May be prepared in advance and refrigerated until ready for baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and cornstarch together.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add butter and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg white to make meringue.

title: country style baked fruit
directions: In a 13 X 9 baking pan, combine apricots, peaches and pineapple, sprinkle on brown sugar.
Dot with butter and add cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Put rice in bottom of baking dish (9 x 13). Add celery and 1/2 onion soup mix. Add cream of mushroom soup, then hot water and mix well. Place chicken on top, then shake the other half of onion soup mix on top of chicken. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cinnamon spread
directions: Beat together until fluffy.
This is great to keep in the refrigerator to use as a spread in making cinnamon toast.
Just take out of refrigerator and spread over your bread and toast.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Cream butter and
sugar
until	smooth.
Beat
in
egg. Stir in other
ingredients.
Chill
and drop by half teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 75 cookies.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and discard juice.
Fold all ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into serving bowl; cover with plastic wrap.
Chill several hours and serve.
Freezes very well.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Brown chicken in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add soup and sour cream slowly until well blended, then add mushroom pieces with juice.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: sour cream chocolate frosting
directions: Mix butter and cooled chocolate thoroughly.
Blend in sifted sugar.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla; beat until frosting is smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute the celery and onion.
Mix everything together and put in casserole. Top with cornflake crumbs.

title: pfannkuchen
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except for seasonal fruits).
Heat 1/4 cup oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Fry a single layer of Pfannkuchen 3 to 5 minutes from both sides until golden brown.
Serve the Pfannkuchen with seasonal fruits.

title: super burger
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Return to pan.
Add additional ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Place chicken breasts in an ungreased baking dish.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese over each piece of chicken.
In a separate bowl, mix together the chicken soup and the white wine.
Pour mixture over the cheese and chicken.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hours.
Serve with rice or angel hair pasta.

title: caramel nut chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine brown sugar, shortening, water and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Beat eggs into
the creamed mixture. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix gradually into the creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Dip tops into chopped pecans.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Press half caramel in center of each cookie.
Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies are set.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove cookies to piece of aluminum foil to cool completely. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: do-drop sandwich spread
directions: Grind ingredients together. Mix well with mayonnaise.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix asparagus, soup, half can French fried onions, cheese and mushrooms in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and sprinkle remaining French fried onions over the top.
Place back in oven long enough for top to brown.

title: low-fat refried beans
directions: Mix Butter Buds according to directions.
Add to pinto beans and mash them.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
You may add any nonfat Cheddar cheese, if you wish.
Fat 0.5 g.
Serves 4.

title: catfish stew
directions: In a large pot, brown fat meat; remove and drain.
Add potatoes and onion to fat remaining in pot.
Cook until tender. Add ketchup.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add fish and remaining ingredients.
Cook at low heat for 45 minutes or until thickened. Enjoy.

title: fudge drops
directions: Place chocolate morsels in a microwave safe bowl.
Microwave at Medium for 2 minutes.
Stir in cereal and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill until firm. Makes 4 dozen.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice to boiling.
Add Jell-O and cool. Whip cream.
Chop celery and nuts.
Blend in and whip softened cream cheese into Jell-O mixture.
Add nuts and celery.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Sets up nicely for Jell-O mold.

title: texas chile
directions: Using cutting board, chop meat into small cubes.
Brown meat in large Dutch oven.
Drain drippings from meat and cover with water. Bring to a boil.
Add salt, pepper, onion, garlic and chili powder. Boil 10 minutes.
Lower heat and simmer for 2 hours.
(Add water as needed.)
Serve with garnish such as grated cheese or chopped cilantro.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Place florets and onion in a bowl and pour dressing over.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle bacon on top and serve!

title: baked pineapple rice
directions: Boil the rice.
Drain the crushed pineapple.
Place in a buttered baking dish 1/4 of the rice; cover with 1/2 of the pineapple.
Repeat the layer.
Place last of rice on top.
Dot each layer with butter and brown sugar.
Pour pineapple juice over top and bake covered for 1 hour, or until brown, at 350°.

title: beginner's white bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 4 cups of flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt. Mix well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill 9 x 13 baking dish level full with apples. Mix 1 cup sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon. Pour over apples. Mix flour, oleo, salt and the 1/2 cup white sugar. Pour over top of apples. Bake at 350° for 1 hour slow.

title: curly mac salad
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients in 1-quart jar.
Shake well; mix with macaroni and vegetables and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Serve cold.

title: cracker bars
directions: Line bottom of cookie sheet with Club crackers.
Boil 7 minutes the oleo, milk, brown sugar and crushed graham crackers. Pour over Keebler crackers.
When cool, top with chips and peanut butter, melted.

title: artichoke heart appetizers
directions: Drain and save juice of 2 (6 ounce) jars artichoke hearts. Mash well and set aside.
Saute onions and garlic.
Add reserved artichoke juice.
Add artichokes, Cheddar cheese, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and eggs.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Top with mixture of bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake 34 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Cool at least 2 hours in refrigerator before cutting into 1-inch squares.
Makes 64.
Serve with fancy toothpicks.

title: 20 minute dutch cake
directions: Beat egg, then sugar, then shortening.
Add milk; mix.
Add flour plus baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
(Batter will be thick.)
Spread batter into a greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Sprinkle batter with enough brown sugar until mostly covered.
Then sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°. Sugar and cinnamon will bubble down into surface.
Best served warm.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool well. Mix softened cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on pretzel crust.
Cool well.
Take jello and boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and strawberries.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: "ole fashion candied yams"
directions: Peel potatoes, slice and put in 8-quart sauce pan along with all ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and let simmer for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Cook and cool crust.
Melt margarine; add nuts and coconut and brown lightly.
Cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put 1/4 cream cheese mixture in each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 caramel, then 1/4 coconut mixture.
Repeat until using all. Freeze.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Pour this mixture in a blender.
Blend about 4 minutes.
Pour in a square dish and refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: chicken livers baked with rice(serving size: 6)
directions: Sprinkle chicken livers with salt and pepper.
Shake with a small amount of flour in a paper or plastic bag.
Brown quickly in butter in a hot skillet.
Place in 6-cup casserole.
Saute onion, celery and rice in butter remaining in skillet until slightly browned.
Add chicken broth to skillet. Stir well.
Add parsley; pour over chicken livers.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Add salt, if needed.

title: pork and rice casserole
directions: Fry and crumble sausage; drain fat.
Stir in all ingredients. Put mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Grated cheese may be added to mix.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pack in a baking dish.

title: corn zucchini bake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg.
Stir in zucchini, onion, butter, milk, corn and cheese.
Pour into greased quart baking dish. Cover and microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until set in center.
Sprinkle with crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika. Microwave one additional minute.
If serving later, microwave an additional 5 minutes before serving.

title: oyster bake
directions: In a
buttered	casserole
(1 quart), alternate oysters and cracker crumbs; dot each layer with butter.
Combine milk, eggs, Worcestershire
sauce and seasonings.
Pour over oysters and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Peel cucumbers and chop into very fine pieces. Blend in cream cheese and add remaining ingredients; mix well. Trim crust from bread slices and cut into 3 pieces. Spread bread sections with cucumber mixture to make small sandwiches.

title: virginia spoon bread
directions: Combine cream, butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Heat until scalding, but do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Using a wooden spoon, beat in the cornmeal, stirring until the mixture is thick.
Beat the egg yolks lightly with the baking powder and pepper.
Stir a small dollop of the hot cornmeal mixture into the yolks to warm them, then stir the yolks into the hot cornmeal.

title: dump cake
directions: Add ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Easy, good and moist.

title: riviera salad
directions: Layer lettuce, fruit and pecans.
Pour dressing on top.

title: cheesy-bacon-baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Pierce with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 55 to 65 minutes or until soft.
Meanwhile, saute bacon in a skillet until brown.
Cool and crumble.
In 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings, cook onions and green pepper until still tender-crisp. Add mushrooms.
Continue sauteing until mushrooms are cooked.
Set aside.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine together.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Yields 6 servings. Calories per serving: 115.
Exchanges: 1 starch, 1 fat.

title: lancashire hot pot
directions: Trim excess fat from meat and coat meat with flour.
In a 5-pint casserole dish, combine floured meat, onions, kidneys, mushrooms, potatoes and stock.
Cover with crust.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove lid and cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: wild rice and hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown the beef.

Saute onion, celery and carrot in margarine. Add soy sauce, salt and pepper, then the cooked rice, mushrooms, water chestnuts and mushroom soup to the ground beef along with sauteed vegetables. Simmer all for 20 to 30 minutes.
Put in a casserole. Add the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple mince muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 18 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; stir only until all ingredients are blended.
Spoon equal portions into prepared muffin tins.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool 1 minute; remove from pan.
Top with Apple Cinnamon Glaze.
Serve warm.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: old fashion peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to sugar mixture and stir until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with floured fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Fill
cupcake pan 2/3 full.
(I use liners in pan.)
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, and egg and blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips and put 1 heaping teaspoon on top of each cupcake. Bake according to directions on package.
Frost with chocolate icing.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook brown sugar and butter until it smokes.
Add cornstarch, egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thick.
Pour in crust.
Mix egg whites and sugar to make meringue.
Spread over pie.
Brown in oven.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Dip fish in batter and deep fry.

title: spinach stuffed manicotti
directions: Drain spinach and mix in large bowl with Ricotta.
Set aside. Combine spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, onion, black olives and green pepper in a medium saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Then add oregano and garlic; continue simmering.
Stuff manicotti shells with spinach/Ricotta mixture.

title: margaret's gingerbread
directions: Mix molasses, brown sugar, Wesson oil and egg until smooth. Sift dry ingredients together and add to above.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle mixed cinnamon and sugar across top before baking.

title: chicken and rice hot dish
directions: Sprinkle rice
in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken pieces.
Mix
together
soups,
milk,
broth
and jam and pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle top with onion soup mix.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.	Serves 8.

title: saskatchewan(sweet and sour spareribs)
directions: Cut ribs in serving pieces and brown well in a frying pan. Mix ingredients and boil over low heat, 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over ribs and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook meat,
onion and green pepper. Drain.
Add rest of ingredients except noodles, pepperoni and cheese. Simmer. Cook noodles and
drain. Layer sauce, noodles, pepperoni and cheese in crock-pot.	Can be put in pan in a slow oven.

title: pan grease
directions: Mix together. This is best stored in Tupperware on shelf. Use when making cakes. Makes a large amount. I usually make 1/2 the recipe. Keeps well.

title: tuna quiche
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, prepare pie crust mix as label directs.
Use to line a 9-inch pie plate.
Spread crust with 1 tablespoon softened butter or margarine.
Preheat oven to 425°. In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, put 3 tablespoons hot butter or margarine; cook onion and pepper until tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove pan from heat; stir in tuna.
Spoon tuna mixture into prepared pie crust.

title: deviled crab cakes
directions: Crumble bread slices.
Add 1/4 pound margarine.
Mix with crab mixture. Dip in egg mixture and bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil to brown.

title: quick dessert
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix on top of the margarine, then sprinkle the coconut and chopped pecans on top of the cake mix.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk over the mixture.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Mix together 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter. Spread on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Pour vegetable oil and water over dry ingredients; mix well.
Spread thinly on sheet (18 x 26-inches).
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 45 minutes, stirring twice to toast evenly.
Let cool.
Serve with milk as a presweetened ready to-eat cereal or serve dry as a snack.

title: applesauce swirl cake
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour half into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Add sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Pour remaining batter over sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
After baking, let set 25 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook the pinwheels in boiling water.
Brown the hamburger, onion, salt and pepper. Boil the pepperoni for 5 minutes to remove grease. Grease a casserole dish. Make layers using 1/2 of each of these ingredients:
pinwheels, then hamburger, tomato sauce, Swiss cheese, pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: doritos chicken
directions: Lightly grease cake pan.
Crush chips.
Boil and bone chicken. Mix soups and tomatoes in bowl.
Layer in pan:
the chicken, 1/2 bag chips, 3/4 of cheese, sauce, 1/2 bag of chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken-cheese bake
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, place chicken and top with cheese. Stir soup and milk and spread over cheese/chicken.

title: fruit delight
directions: Start with layer of cookies; crumbled.
Then put the fruit, Cool Whip and repeat.
You may use any fruit that is in season. If you use fresh strawberries, put enough sugar in to make juice.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients at medium speed until smooth.
Pour into a greased spring-form pan, dusted with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn oven off and let stand in oven an additional 2 hours.
Cover with a pie filling when cool, if desired.

title: nanaimo bars(pronounced na-ni-mo)
directions: Mix the 1/2 cup butter, white sugar, egg and cocoa.
Set over boiling water and stir until mixture resembles a custard.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine stuffing mix, cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken in butter and roll in stuffing mixture.
Place in large shallow pan, skin side up.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake at 370° for 1 hour.

title: quick fruit punch
directions: Prepare soft drink mix as package directs.
(Add 1 cup sugar if unsweetened mix is used.)
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Chill. Add ginger ale and almond extract just before serving.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: butterscotch nut bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour; mix.
Add pecans.
Pour in a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool; ice with icing mix.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Form balls.
Press with fork dipped in flour. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine and pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Add ingredients in order.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, let cool and cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soups, sour cream, onion flakes and 1 stick margarine together in bowl.
Mix in potatoes.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Roll out 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Mix another stick margarine.
Add 2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese and top with buttered corn flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Prepare spaghetti sauce.
Prepare shells as label directs. Drain well in colander.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine Ricotta and next 6 ingredients.
Stuff rounded tablespoonful of cheese mixture into each shell.
Spoon 3/4 cup sauce into each of two 13 x 19-inch baking dishes.
Place shells, seam side down, over sauce in one layer. Spoon over remaining sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: coconut cream pie trifle(ritz cracker dessert)
directions: Mix butter, coconut, pecans and crackers together with a fork. Save 1/2 of mixture for topping. Mix milk, pudding and ice cream together until thickened.

title: chile corn spoon bread
directions: In large saucepan over medium-high heat, heat water and milk almost to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Using a whisk, slowly stir in cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, garlic powder and black pepper until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart souffle or baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until puffed
and golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour and shortening, then add other ingredients.
Roll and make crust.

title: quick and easy ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix half and half, whipping cream, eggs, flour, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Divide ham and cheese and put in the bottom of both pie shells.
Divide egg mixture and pour over ham and cheese. Put both pies in 375 degree preheated oven and bake for 40 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan, salt, pepper, parsley, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then in crumbs mixture.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: spaetzle
directions: Beat egg well.
Add flour, water and salt, stirring to a stiff, smooth batter.
Drop batter from tip of spoon, 1/2 teaspoon at a time, into boiling water.
Cook until spaetzle comes to surface.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Transfer to goulash.

title: crumbly peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg; cut in margarine with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle half of the mixture in the pastry shell; arrange peaches, cut side down, over crumb mixture, then add remaining crumbs over peaches.
Add water; bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slightly thaw potatoes.
Combine with 1/2 cup butter, salt and pepper.
Add cheese, soup, onion and sour cream; blend well.
Top with corn flakes; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: banana berry shake
directions: In blender container or food processor bowl with metal blade, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth.
Makes 1 (1 2/3 cup) serving.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as directed. Cook spinach and cool. Add cheese, pepper and salt. Mix well; stuff shells. Brown beef; mix with spaghetti sauce. Place stuffed shells in shallow baking pan. Pour beef and spaghetti sauce over shells. Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Can season sauce as desired.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix at medium speed syrup, sugar, salt, margarine and vanilla. Add slightly beaten eggs and mix well.
Add 1 cup pecans to mixture.
Put remaining cup of pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check several times as it may not take as long to bake.

title: hawaii hamburger
directions: Combine milk, onions, crumbs and meat.
Form into balls with a pineapple chunk inside each.
Brown meatballs in small amount of oil in large skillet.
Drain pineapple and save syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.

title: funnel cakes(makes 12)
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Sift dry ingredients together; add eggs and milk.
Mix. Beat until smooth.
Let stand.
Heat 3 to 4-inches deep fat to 375°.
Pour batter into pitcher; pour some through funnel and swirl until cake is 3-inches diameter.
Fry until golden.
Drain.
Serve with syrup and honey for breakfast.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Fill greased casserole	1/2
full
with sliced or diced potatoes.
Combine next
7 ingredients and pour over potatoes. Top with cheese and
bread
crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 large pans.
When cake is done and while hot, mix sugar and lemon juice and sprinkle over cake.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oatmeal.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in prepared pan, 9 x 13-inch, and bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
After cake cools, spread topping over (receipt follows) and place under broiler until it caramelizes.

title: jigglers creamy
directions: Stir the boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely. Cool to room temperature (about 30 minutes).
Pour milk into mixing bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Quickly pour into gelatin.
Stir with wire whisk until well blended.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm (3 hours).

title: collard greens
directions: Pick, clean, wash and cut up greens.
In skillet, put oil and saute onion and garlic.
Put greens in pot on top of sauteed onions and garlic with 1 cup of water.
Cook at moderate heat and add salt to taste.
Cook until done.
Do not burn.
If needs more water, add just enough to keep from burning.
Same can be done with mustard and turnip greens.

title: chocolate mint layer cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo over low heat.
Mix sugar and flour, then add to chocolate mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix well and shape in rolls; cool overnight and slice and bake in moderate oven.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Place a layer of vegetables in Dutch oven, roasting pan or slow cooker.
Add 1/2 the soups, 1/2 the soup mix and 1/2 the meat; repeat.
Add water.
Cover; bake in conventional oven at 300° for 5 hours or in slow cooker for 6 to 8 hours.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Put the crushed Oreo cookies on the bottom of a cake pan, then mix all the other ingredients together, then put it down over the Oreos, then put the rest of the Oreos on top.

title: smashed potato and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place potatoes in a saucepan, cover with water.
Cook 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes reserving 1 cup cooking liquid.
Return potatoes and liquid to pan.
Mash with potato masher until slightly chunky.
Add chopped broccoli and next 6 ingredients to pan.
Stir well.
Spoon into an 11 x 7 inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts. 6 servings.

title: deep-dish cheesecake coffee cake(breakfast cheesecake)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a bowl; stir vigorously 30 seconds.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 4 or 5 times.
Pat evenly in the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch round cake pan or pie pan; set aside.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with vegetables.

title: macaroni and chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 60 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water for 5 minutes; stir in flour, salt, soda, baking powder and sugar together.
Add shortening.
Combine yeast and buttermilk; add to flour mixture slowly, stirring with fork.
Turn onto floured board and knead.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: olive tarts
directions: Mix together and mold around olives.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put water, celery and potatoes in large pot; boil 5 minutes. Add milk, broth and soup.
Bring back to boil.
Saute onion in melted butter.
Add flour and mix well.
Add to first mixture. Add Cheez Whiz, salt, pepper and mustard.
Bring to slow boil and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Remove seasoning packet from noodles.
Set aside.
Crush noodles.
Combine noodles and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine seasoning packet with remaining ingredients.
Mix with wire whisk.
Pour dressing over cabbage.
Toss gently to coat. Cover and chill.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crumble Oreos; add margarine and mix.
Set aside 3/4 cup for topping. Press the rest into a 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.
Mix the pudding, using only 3 1/2 cups of milk; set it aside.
Whip the cream cheese until fluffy; add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add pudding and beat together until well blended.
Pour over Oreo crust.
Sprinkle with reserved cookie crumbles.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut.
Spread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package, except use milk instead of water.
Pour in pan over nuts and coconut.
Whip together cream cheese, sour cream, margarine, sugar and vanilla. Pour gently over cake batter.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Take out of oven and leave in pan for 15 minutes.
Then turn out on waxed paper.

title: peanut-butter chocolate chip crisscrosses
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs and beat thoroughly. Stir in peanut butter.

title: stuffed pork chops(microwave)
directions: In a mixing bowl, heat milk and butter together, about 1 minute and 30 seconds or until butter melts.
Add bread stuffing and stir until moistened.
(For ease in sprinkling gravy mix, pour into a salt shaker.)
Sprinkle one side of 4 chops with gravy mix, placing that side down in a shallow pie plate or baking dish. Spoon 1/2 cup stuffing on each chop.
Top with other four chops, sprinkling top side with remaining gravy mix.
Cook, uncovered, for 12 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: east indian chicken
directions: Drain peaches, saving 1/4 cup syrup.
Melt butter or margarine in saucepan; add curry and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in onions, vinegar and reserved syrup.
Baste chicken with sauce and place on roasting pan lined with aluminum foil. Bake at 400° for 1 hour, basting and turning every 15 minutes. Add peach halves.
Baste with sauce and bake 10 minutes longer. Serves 4.

title: frosting frome rose
directions: Add this to paste.
Beat all with an electric mixer.
Be sure cake is cool.

title: honey butter
directions: Combine butter and honey in small bowl.
Stir with wooden spoon until thoroughly blended.

title: chicken biscuit pie
directions: In skillet, blend soups and 1 cup milk.
Add chicken, peas, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Combine biscuit mix, 2/3 cup milk and melted butter.
Drop by teaspoon onto hot chicken mixture.
Bake in hot oven (450°) until biscuits are lightly browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into long roll.
Roll in chili powder.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion and cook.
Add sauces.
Mix and cook for 5 minutes.
In another pan, mix the 2 cans of soup and chilies and heat over low heat for 10 minutes (or less time if using microwave).

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix as directed on box, then stir in Cool Whip. Cut up bananas into the mix, then stir in vanilla wafers. Makes a big bowl full.

title: sweet potato custard pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then about 40 to 45 minutes at 350° until center is set and tests done.

title: foil dinners
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place frozen peas in colander and run cold water over just until broken apart.
Tear off 4 pieces of heavy-duty foil, each about 18 x 15-inch.
On the center of each, place pieces of carrot, potato and meat.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Spoon over foil mixtures.
Top with peas.
Close foil securely.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 50 minutes or until meat is done.

title: cocktail slush
directions: Mix together and freeze to make a slush.

title: lottie's salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Pour into oblong dish and sprinkle top with 1/2 box of lime Jell-O. Store in refrigerator.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well. Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add 1/2 of flour mixture to creamed ingredients.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour and stir well.
Add chips.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: small dinner rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape down the sides of bowl with paddle scraper.
Seal and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Punch down and turn out on pastry sheet.
Make into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring water, cream of tartar and sugar to boil.
Drop in 18 Ritz crackers.
Do not stir.
Boil 10 minutes on low heat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 275° until done.
Check at 20 to 25 minutes.

title: simply apple salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients; mix well.
Blend next four ingredients and pour over apple mix and place in fridge, covered.

title: apple dobble cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add other ingredients, gradually, except apples.
Fold in apples. Bake in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: banana nut pie
directions: Cream sugar with butter; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir bananas and lemon juice.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix quickly; stir in nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until done when tested; cool on rack.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; rinse well and drain.
Place in crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook 8 to 12 hours.

title: sausage delight
directions: You will need one 18 x 9 x 2-inch stainless steel pan.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Best if made the day before.

title: vernell's beans and rice
directions: Saute
red
beans,
garlic,
chopped onions, parsley and pepper in
oil
for 15 minutes.
Add 3 1/2 cups water or broth. Bring to
boil.
Add
2 1/2 cups of rice, cook until all liquid is absorbed or until rice is tender.
Serve with gravy or roux.

title: anna's broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°, or until brown.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Boil juice for 3 minutes.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add cranberry sauce and
mix well with the juice and jello.
Chill until very thick; add Cool Whip and mix well.
Keep chilled.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Chop onion and pepper.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
Mix onion, pepper, soup and juice.
Pour over egg noodles and meat.
Stir until well mixed.
Top with cheese and bake at approximately 350° until cheese is bubbling hot and melted.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 stick of oleo, melted.
Make a crust in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs, powdered sugar and rest of oleo for at least 15 minutes.
Spread on top of crust.
Cover with thin banana slices.
Add crushed pineapple; cover with whipped cream.
Garnish with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown (saute) ground beef.
Add onion and garlic.
Drain off all grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Layer meat sauce, flour tortillas, 1 pint sour cream, 2 cups grated Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers twice.
Bake at 325° until hot and cheese melts.

title: "kiss" cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Slowly stir in sugar and chips.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet in the shape of Hershey's Kisses.
Bake at 315° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Yield:
2 sheets.

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix all
ingredients together.	Put in shaker for table use. Excellent for salt restricted diets.

title: tropical fruit dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, lime juice, honey, cumin and pepper sauce; mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve with cut up fresh fruit.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: aunt charlotte's ketchup dip
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch glass dish for best appearance.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together and pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Good luck.

title: snappy tomato
directions: Put in buttered baking dish. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: In saucepan, add flour and milk.
Cook until thick.
Let cool. In separate bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla.
Combine all ingredients together and beat.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Combine apples with celery and add mayo.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat milk to boiling point.
Mix the sugar, spices and salt.
Mix everything together.
Pour into crust.
(Taste to see if it needs a tad more sugar.) Bake for 15 minutes.
Turn oven back to 350° and let cook for 20 to 25 more minutes, or until set.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Add shortening and sugar to milk; cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup milk mixture.
Add black pepper, salt and soda to remaining milk.
Add flour to make a spongy dough.
Let rise until double. Punch down until double knead.
Shape into rolls.
Bake in greased pans at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove seeds from pepper; parboil 10 minutes and drain.
Brown meat; drain.
Add 1 can tomatoes, bread crumbs and seasoning; mix well.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Blend cornstarch with second can of tomatoes.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Pour over peppers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tender.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Pour into large bowl.
Add flour and nuts; mix by hand.
Roll out into small balls; cook until light brown.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar. Makes about 10 to 12 dozen.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cut a deep pocket in side of each chicken breast at its thickest part.
Fold a ham slice around a cheese slice; tuck in pocket.
Skewer with toothpicks to secure.
Combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in butter, then in bread crumbs. Place in buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Brush with butter from pan if chicken becomes too dry.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, bacon, raisins and onion in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over salad. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together yellow
cake mix, margarine and 1 egg; mix well. Add coconut and pecans.
Press mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix
topping of powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese. Pour over
cake before baking.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken from the oven
directions: Spray Pam in rectangular pan.
Mix flour and seasonings.
Coat chicken with mixture.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and bake until tender.

title: springtime soup
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add all ingredients, except asparagus/spinach.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add asparagus/spinach; stir well.
Take off heat.
Serve.

title: apple pie
directions: Cut in blocks fresh apples in uncooked pie shell.
Then mix sugar, flour, egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over apples.
Dot with butter and bake at 375° until done.

title: luau slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 15-inch pan or Ziploc bags.
Freeze until firm.
Thirty to 45 minutes before serving, stir.
Serve with spoon and enjoy.

title: raspberry ring
directions: Pour boiling liquid over gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in raspberry sherbet until melted. Pour into 4-cup ring mold and chill.

title: country-style stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove tops, seeds and membranes from peppers.
Crumble sausage into skillet.
Cook with onion.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato and 1 1/2 cups
cheese.
Fill peppers with mixture; top with remaining cheese.
Arrange in 9-inch square baking pan. Add 1/4 cup water.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice continental
directions: Saute crushed garlic and mushrooms in small amount of oil in skillet.
Remove garlic pieces.
Add chicken, stirring, until lightly browned.
Add broth, green beans and seasonings; bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: firni(rice pudding)
directions: Soak the rice in water until fairly soft, then grind to paste. Bring milk to boil.
Add sugar and rice paste, stirring until well blended.
Cook on low fire until desired consistency is reached. Chill before serving.
Garnish with fine shredded pistachios and almonds.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine lettuce, onion, chili beans and cheese.
Add tomatoes and Fritos just before serving.
Toss salad with dressing.
Yields 20 servings.

title: rocky's salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add all ingredients together.
(Mix canned milk with mayo.)
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Add more mayo if desired.

title: rum pudding(rompudding)
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for about 5 minutes.
Dissolve completely over hot water.
Beat eggs until foamy; add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add gelatin, salt and rum.
Cool in refrigerator until mixture begins to thicken.
Add whipped cream, gently folding into mixture.
Chill until firm. Serve with a sauce made of sweetened fruit (raspberries thickened with cornstarch).

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well and bake in a 450° oven, until thoroughly done.
Cut potatoes lengthwise, scoop out the pulp and mash with butter, cream, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Add onions. Fill the reserved shells with the mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cauliflower.
Break into bite-size pieces. Add onion, bell pepper and mayonnaise.
Beat together mayonnaise, sugar and sour cream; add to vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet and brown meatballs. Remove and pour off excess fat.
Heat jelly and chili sauce, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until thoroughly coated.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: jean leflar's corn cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Good.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan. Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto batter.
Cut through batter with a knife several times.
Sprinkle with additional chocolate chips and chopped nuts if desired.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the nuts and parsley.
Shape into ball.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Mix nuts and parsley; coat ball.

title: barbecue jack pots
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Spray muffin pans with cooking spray.
Add remaining ingredients to meat. Stuff biscuits in muffin pan.
Add mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Put 1/2 of it in a baked 9-inch pie crust.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour, milk, butter, vanilla, beaten yolks and salt.
Cook until smooth; cool slightly. Pour into pie crust.
Put rest of peanut butter mixture on top. Beat egg whites, 1/2 cup sugar, cream of tartar and cornstarch together.
Put on top of pie and bake at 350° until browned.

title: mexican vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables all together, then heat water, sugar and vinegar and pour over vegetables. Mix well with vegetables, then put in fridge. Better if made 6 to 8 hours before serving. Gets better with age. Will last 2 weeks or more in refrigerator. Serves 30 to 50 people.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine tomatoes, celery, onion, green pepper and seasonings.
Cook gently for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Saute garlic and onion in small amount of fat.
Brown lean ground beef.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, onion-garlic mixture, parsley, sugar, salt and ground basil and cook until thick.
Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions.

title: ting's dip(serves 20 +)
directions: Mix and put in ovenproof dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter; add the chopped nuts and spread over beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take kitchen shears and cut the dried beef in small pieces before mixing with the cheese and other ingredients.
Serve with dip-sized Fritos.
This dip is excellent for dance refreshments.

title: cornflake crunchies
directions: Mix light corn syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Let come to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal and mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.

title: grandma's gelatin fruit salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 1 cup hot water and lemon Jell-O. Add 1 cup ice cubes; stir until melted.
Add pineapple.
Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Repeat with orange gelatin, 1 cup hot water and 1 cup ice.
Stir in mini marshmallows.
Pour over lemon layer and refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over all other ingredients.
Mix lightly.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate morsels over hot, not boiling, water or melt in microwave until smooth.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in an 8-inch pan.
Let stand until firm; cut into squares.

title: sour cream oven donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients into a soft dough.
Smooth into a ball. On a floured board, knead 10 times and roll to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Place donuts onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Spread lettuce in bottom of baking pan. Mix seasoning and cream cheese with meat.
Spread mixture on top of lettuce; slice tomatoes and put on top of meat.
Crush Doritos on top.
Put in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: festive peach passover cake
directions: Drain peaches very well.
Reserve a few slices.
Dice remainder.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Mix with Matzo meal and granulated sugar.
Reserve a few tablespoons mixture.
Press remainder on bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan or 8 x 1 1/2-inch layer cake pan with removable bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Cream remaining butter; add powdered sugar gradually, beating until smooth and fluffy. Gradually beat in egg yolks, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Turn into pan over crust.
Top with diced peaches.
Lightly blend remaining lemon rind with sour cream.
Spread over peaches. Sprinkle with reserved Matzo meal mixture; garnish with reserved peaches.
Chill several hours until firm.
Remove sides of pan; place cake on serving platter.

title: world's best sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oleo and oil until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together salt, soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Roll into balls and press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pork chop and cabbage dinner
directions: In a 12-inch ovenproof skillet, cook pork chops in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Remove from skillet and add onion, cooking until tender.
Stir in wine, brown sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir in cabbage and apples.
Bring mixture to a boil. Top with chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.

title: strawberry frozen salad
directions: To cream cheese, add sugar.
Mix together and set aside.

title: connie's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each one.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Bake in floured and greased large tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Start in cold oven.)

title: sliced baked potatoes(heart smart)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel potatoes; slice lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Put potatoes in pan, turning them over to coat both sides with margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 3 greased loaf pans.

title: beet relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in jars; seal.

title: arkansas duck casserole
directions: Cook ducks with sliced onion and celery in enough water to cover for 2 hours or until tender.
Remove from bones and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook rice in liquid from duck.
Saute chopped onion in butter in a skillet.
Stir in flour; add mushrooms and liquid, milk, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in rice and duck; place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: val's beef stew
directions: Put meat in pan and brown in some oil.
Add barley, onions, carrots and potatoes.
Add enough water to cover with 2 inches more, add beef bouillon and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil, turn heat down and simmer for 1 to 1-1/2 hours.
When the potatoes and carrots are almost done add canned or frozen vegetables of choice. Let cook to a boil again and then add the instant potatoes to the consistency you want.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, seasoning salt, garlic salt, onion salt and add a little love!
If you don't have instant potatoes you can take 1 cup cold water and mix about 2-3 TBSP flour or corn starch to thicken.
Add to mixture when it boils again.
I like to make some biscuits or cornbread to serve with it.
It is also good with some sliced cheese or jelly for the biscuits.
This is a great recipe to do in the crock pot.

title: mousse in a minute
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package but use 2 1/4 cups of milk.
Fold in whipped topping and spoon into dessert dishes.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Soften ice cream.
Stir in Cool Whip and crushed Oreo cookies. Pour into bowl and freeze.

title: apple-cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Add juices. Mix well.
Add fruit (nuts would be added here as well).
Chill until set.

title: gingerbread with hard sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg and sugar until light.
Add butter, beating constantly.
Sift together dry ingredients into bowl.
Mix wet ingredients well.
Add dry and wet ingredients, alternating 1/3 at a time.
Beat really well with a wooden spoon. With rubber spatula, scrape into greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour; cool.

title: jail house rolls
directions: Mix dry yeast and lukewarm water; blend and set aside. Combine potatoes, oleo, eggs, salt and sugar. Blend in the flour. Add the yeast mixture and work all together until well blended. Put into a large greased bowl. Cover with a cold damp cloth and put into the refrigerator until one is ready to make rolls. Punch down dough and knead it. Put on a slightly floured board and roll it out like one would biscuits. Do not have it too thin. Cut rolls with a biscuit cutter. Place on a greased pan, not too close together. Butter tops and let rise several hours or until doubled in bulk and light. If one wants rolls to be browned on all sides, they must be far enough apart not to touch after they have risen. Bake in a 450° oven from 10 to 15 minutes.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in water.
Add raspberries and lemon juice to water and stir until berries thaw.
Chill until partially set.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar, vanilla and salt together.
Fold in a small amount of whipped heavy cream to the cream cheese mixture, then fold in the rest.
Spread 1/2 white layer over bottom of baked pie shell.
Cover this with 1/2 red jello mixture.
Repeat layers.
Chill until set.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars together until creamy.
Add egg.
Mix in flour, soda, salt and vanilla into the creamy mixture and stir until well mixed.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drop by balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 to 5 dozen.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter in mixer.
Gradually add flour and nuts.
Shape into logs; wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until firm. Slice and arrange on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 20 minutes in a 325° oven, until slightly browned (depends on thickness of slices).

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Blend or process all ingredients.
Start with only 1 1/2 teaspoon of horseradish and add more to suit your taste.
Chill well.
Serve with crackers.
