Makes approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: yellow spring cake
directions: Mix and bake yellow cake mix as directed on box. Simmer 20 ounce can of crushed pineapple with 1/2 to all of its juice and 1 cup sugar until it thickens slightly. When cake is done, punch holes in top and pour hot pineapple mixture over cake. Refrigerate until chilled. Mix 1 small box instant vanilla pudding and pour over top; chill. Cover with Cool Whip and chopped nuts. Keep refrigerated.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Mix flour, soda and spices. Add alternately with sour cream, beginning with and ending with dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in large pan 30-35 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon sugar muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into lined muffin cups.
Sprinkle with mixture of 3 tablespoons oleo (softened), 4 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes until done.
Makes 12 to 16 muffins.

title: biscuits
directions: Mash flour and butter with fork until thoroughly mixed.
Add milk.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown and toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pans after 8 minutes.

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove and immediately sprinkle with marshmallows. Return to oven 1 to 2 minutes until marshmallows puff.
Remove and cool.

title: italian beef pie
directions: Season meat and brown along with onion.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix meat, broccoli, soup and sour cream.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: reese's squares
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together 2 minutes.
Pour liquid over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: surprise dessert
directions: Mix together in large bowl. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over boiling water.
Cream butter and sugar. Then add egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Add melted chocolate to butter and eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add alternately with buttermilk, beating well by hand, then add pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or longer in long pan or round for layers.

title: italian crostini
directions: Mix all ingredients but bread.
Put bread slices on baking sheet and spread each with 1/2 tablespoon of the olive mixture. Heat broiler and toast until golden brown and cheese bubbles, about 3 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Brown corned beef, green pepper and onion in melted shortening.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cover; bring mixture to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 beef barbecues.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt 1 stick of oleo and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: zucchini-oatmeal muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, beat eggs slightly. Stir in sugar, oil and zucchini. Add all the dry ingredients (batter will be lumpy). Spoon batter into muffin tins or cupcake papers in a cupcake pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove muffins from pans. Serve warm.
These can be reheated in the microwave, too.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar. Continue creaming until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes. Cool 2 hours.
Remove from pan and cool completely before serving. Powdered sugar on top optional.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Take Pyrex dish.
Add the 2 cans of white meat chicken (drained), then add cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup. Mix well.
Add rice.
Combine with mayonnaise.
Blend all the ingredients well.
After ingredients are blended, add saltine cracker crumbs to the top of the dish.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place in oven and let dish cook for 30 minutes.
Serve dish whenever desired.

title: famous amos chocolate peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium size bowl combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed beat butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla about 3 minutes, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat until thoroughly blended after each addition.
Reduce speed to low; gradually add flour mixture until smooth.
Stir peanut butter cup pieces into dough along with chocolate chips. Drop dough, 3 tablespoons per cookie, onto ungreased cookie sheet, about 1 inch apart.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes until dry and slightly firm to touch.
Let cookies cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Using metal spatula, remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.
Per cookie: 313 calories, 7 g protein, 18 g fat, 35 g carbohydrates, 183 mg sodium, 44 mg cholesterol.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, molasses and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill dough overnight.
Preheat oven to 375°. Grease cookie sheet. Form dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Leave on cookie sheet for a few minutes (it makes it easier to lift them). Makes 4 dozen.

title: lime ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Cool and add ginger ale.
When slightly thickened, add celery, apples and nut meats.
Chill and serve on lettuce with mayonnaise thinned with a fruit juice.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together and refrigerate 24 hours.
Form into ball and roll in chopped walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until mixture forms a firm ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites.
Add syrup mixture slowly. Keep beating until mixture is cool.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop from spoon on waxed paper.

title: oreo pie
directions: Mix Oreo cookies (crushed) with margarine and press in bottom of large dish.
Mix pudding, cream cheese, milk and softened Cool Whip.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Sprinkle reserved crumbs over pie (about 1 cup).

title: fairy dusted spinach salad
directions: Toss muffin cubes with dressing and cheese.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until browned.
Stir occasionally.
Combine spinach, onion, mushrooms and bacon.
Add dressing, cheese and croutons.
Toss lightly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sandy's pistachio cake
directions: Beat until thick and spread over cake.
Cake must then be refrigerated.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat and onions together, adding garlic and red pepper to taste.
Combine beans, tomato juice, tomatoes, meat and onions in pot.
Add 10 teaspoons chili powder (or to taste).
Simmer two hours.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Cube cheese and slice onions. Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 275°.

title: buffet party seafood
directions: Melt butter in large pot over moderate heat.
Stir in onions, green peppers and mushrooms.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper smoothly.
Stir in milk gradually.
Return pan to heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in cheese and mix. Add lemon juice, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until cheese melts.
Break seafood into bite size pieces and add to mixture.
Mix and let mixture heat to a boil.
Serve over pastry shells or macaroni.
Add parsley as a garnish.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream together first 5 ingredients.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt, oatmeal and nuts together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix until all ingredients are coated.

title: pork and apple casserole
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper to taste.
Brown chops on both sides in a skillet.
Place chops in a large shallow casserole.
Save fat drippings in the skillet.
Peel and cut apples into 1/4 inch slices; arrange on the chops.
Pour molasses over all.
Stir flour into fat in the skillet.
Cook and stir until brown.
Slowly stir in hot water and cook until mixture boils.

title: christmas meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs in shortening.
Drain and then cook in roast beef gravy or great gravy for meatballs.
If making large amount, place in roaster and roast in 350° oven until meat is cooked through.
At Christmas, our family places one meatball on a piece of buttered lefse, with a small amount of gravy, rolls it up and enjoys.

title: summer squash haystacks
directions: Coarsely shred assorted summer squash.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and squash; saute until squash is tender (2 to 3 minutes).
Add teriyaki sauce; toss to combine.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream the shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in the blueberries.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields about 2 dozen.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces, put in pie shell.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over rhubarb.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 325° until set.

title: naida's italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes in microwave.
Bake for approximately one hour in regular oven.
Heat small amount of spaghetti sauce and spread on meat loaf when done.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix margarine and cheese.
Add flour and Rice Krispies.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Roll into small balls.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: taco biscuit bites
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add biscuit mix, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Brush tops with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
About 1 1/2 dozen.

title: grilled fish steaks with ginger, honey and mustard
directions: Combine mustard, mayonnaise, ginger and honey in bowl.
In a large, shallow dish, coat fish with mustard mixture on both sides. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate 30 minutes in refrigerator while preparing grill.
When coals are hot, grill fish on oiled grid, about 5 minutes per side, turning once.
Serves 4.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans until soft.
Brown meat.
Add all ingredients together.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg together. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, then jam.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to batter alternately with buttermilk.
Dust nuts with flour and stir in.
Pour into three 8-inch greased and floured (bottom only) cake tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Mix well.
Add drained potatoes. Turn into prepared casserole.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top. Drizzle melted oleo over all.
Bake for 1 hour.
Excellent side dish.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350° F.
Lightly grease a shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Melt butter, toss with cracker crumbs to moisten evenly. Whisk soup mix, dry mustard and nutmeg in large bowl to blend. Whisk in cream, eggs and egg yolks until very well blended.

Stir in remaining ingredients and pour all into prepared baking dish. Sprinkle cracker crumb mixture on pudding near edges of dish. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until a knife inserted near center comes out clean and temperature of center registers 160° on an instant meat thermometer.
(Center will jiggle when dish is moved, that's ok.) Serves 12.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil, sour cream and eggs until creamy. In a small bowl, mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour half the batter into pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
Cut into batter.
Pour rest of batter into pan and top with remaining brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Insert knife to see if done.
If not, bake for 5 minute intervals until done.
Cool for 20 minutes and flip on serving dish.

title: scotch egg slices
directions: Divide raw sausage into 6 equal parts.
Pat one part evenly around each peeled egg with wet hands.
Mix bread crumbs, marjoram, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Dip sausage coated egg into beaten egg, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Heat oil (1 1/2 inches) in 3-quart saucepan to 360°.
Fry 3 eggs at time, turning occasionally, 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Refrigerate until cold enough to sliced (2 hours).
Cut each egg crosswise into 4 sections.
Serve with Dijon style mustard.

title: lemon bread
directions: Squeeze the lemon and mix with 1/2 cup sugar (lemon glaze).

title: light rolls
directions: Scald milk and let cool.
Stir in sugar, shortening and salt. Dissolve yeast in warm water and beat in egg. Combine with milk and beat well.
Sift in flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Mix well and place in a greased bowl. Cover and allow to rise. Spoon into muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove from bones.
Mix dressing and butter.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into greased baking dish and add a layer of chicken.
Mix chicken soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Use remaining dressing mixture on top.
Pour chicken broth over contents of casserole and bake at 350° (177°C) for 30 minutes or until top browns.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Place strawberries in blender with sugar or sweetener.
Blend until smooth.
Add wine and blend.
Remove strawberry mixture to large bowl.
Whip two egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into strawberries.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve in wide mouth champagne glass.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 4 (6 x 3 x 2-inch) foil pans. In medium bowl, stir flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl at medium speed, beat sugar, oil and eggs until blended.
Add bananas.
Beat until well blended.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and soak eggplant in salt water for 6 to 12 hours, overnight
if
possible.
Soak
bread
crumbs
in milk.
Saute onions,
celery and bell pepper in oleo for 15 minutes.
Place eggplant
in
a
large pan to boil covered with water and cook until almost done.	Mix bread crumbs, sauteed ingredients, and eggplant
together.
Add eggs, pimiento and seasonings.
Blend well.
Place
in
a
baking
dish
and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake
in
a
350°	oven until golden brown.
Serve at once
or
keep
in	a
warm oven until ready to serve, not too long.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Place spareribs, cut in small pieces, in a large frying pan and cover with hot water.
Bring to boil.
Drain and dry throughly.
Add oil to frying pan and when hot, add the spareribs and brown thoroughly.
Drain oil.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Grease 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 150° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: rell's christmas candy
directions: Mix well the sugar, oleo and milk and add the coconut and pecans.
Mix well and roll into balls.
Put into refrigerator until hard.

title: butter frosting
directions: Cream butter.
Add about 1/2 the sugar, blending well.
Beat in 2 tablespoons cream and vanilla.
Gradually blend in remaining sugar.
Add enough cream to make of spreading consistency.
Frosts one 9 x 13-inch or 2 (8 to 9-inch) layers.

title: mandy lombardo's chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Over medium heat, mix the sugar and soy sauce; stir.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a foamy boil and pour chicken wings in a baking pan.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting every 15 minutes.

title: sorrell ridge blueberry muffins
directions: The trick to great muffins is a light hand.
Never overmix and never use an electric beater or blender.

title: mrs. t's apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixed with baking powder.
Beat ingredients together and spread in 8-inch square cake pan, greased and floured.
Slice seasonal fruit (apples, peaches or plums) and place down on top of cake.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with pieces of butter on top of cake.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: honey pecan cake
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon vinegar and enough milk to make 1 cup; set aside.
Stir cooking oil into sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed of electric mixer.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.
Beat 1 minute more.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Poke holes in hot cake.
Drizzle with honey syrup:
Boil together 1/4 cup honey, 1 teaspoon water and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Cut frozen bread dough into about 6 to 8 portions.
Roll out dough and add 2 teaspoons Mozzarella and 8 slices of pepperoni to each and roll up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Heat in a 375° oven for 25 minutes. Bread will be brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbs.
Save one cup for topping.
Press the rest of mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg together.
Pour over baked mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake 15 minutes longer at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.
Best if set in the refrigerator a couple of hours before cutting.
Can be made a day ahead of time.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow baking pan.
Combine butter and seasonings, mixing well; brush on chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 2 servings.
May be doubled. Chicken breasts can be substituted.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup together in a 1-quart measuring cup or a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Put in microwave for 4 minutes on High. Take out and add 1/2 cup peanuts and stir.
Put back in microwave for 3 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out; add butter and vanilla and stir.
Put back in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out; add baking soda and stir quickly.
It will get foamy right away, then pour into a greased cookie sheet or cake pan.
Cool for at least 15 minutes, then it should be hard and can be cut or broken in pieces by hand.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Coat a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine the stuffing mix, water, butter, cranberries, and corn; mix well. Place 1/4 cup of the stuffing mixture at the smaller end of each turkey slice and roll up crepe-style.
Place in the baking dish seam side down, forming 2 rows of 6 rolls.
Spoon the gravy over the turkey rolls, then cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until heated through.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple and 2 large ripe bananas.
Pour 1/2 into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread evenly 1 cup sour cream over this.
Pour remaining jello on top.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, or put in small crockette pot.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in broccoli, carrots, onion, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Add pea pods and cashews.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Add wine, if desired.

title: french toast delight
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir. In a skillet on medium heat, place a teaspoon of margarine until melted.
Dip bread into egg mixture on both sides.
Cook on both sides until golden brown.
Repeat until all batter is used.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium sized bowl, combine soup, celery, onion, paprika and croutons.
Spoon the mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange the chicken over the mixture, pressing it lightly into the mixture.
In a cup, combine the brown sugar and mustard.
Spread evenly over the chicken. Bake for 30 minutes or until chicken is done (no pink juice remains).

title: restaurant style biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix soda into buttermilk.
Add liquids to flour.
Put in refrigerator until needed.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: chili(mildly seasoned)
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer from 1 to 2 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins. Cube and arrange in layers in greased baking dish, covering each layer with grated cheese and white sauce.
On top, cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: 4th of july chicken or ribs
directions: You will need a squeeze spray bottle.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Bring sugar, water and salt to hard ball stage or 250° on candy thermometer.
Put Marshmallow Creme in mixing bowl and stir in hot syrup.
Beat until stiff and stands in peaks.
Fold in vanilla and pecans.
Drop by spoonful onto plate or wax paper.

title: cucumber strips
directions: Peel, seed cucumbers, cut in strips and put in churn; cover with water and lime.
Let stand overnight, rinse 3 times in cold water.
Let stand in ice water for 4 hours.

title: pioneer bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixer bowl.
Add sugar, salt, egg, shortening, 1/3 cup cornmeal and 1 cup of the flour.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mash with fork into small pan that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread crescent rolls on large cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over cooled crust.
Add fresh vegetables on top: cucumbers, radishes, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, celery, cherry tomatoes, etc.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll and shape into small balls with hands or in food processor.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden.
May be frozen.
Yields 75 balls.

title: minted or malted cocoa
directions: Stir malted milk powder or peppermint extract into hot chocolate; blend together in saucepan and heat well.
Garnish malted cocoa with marshmallows; serve minted cocoa topped with whipped cream and a sprig of mint or a peppermint stick stirrer. Serves 2.

title: chicken dip
directions: Fry chicken and season to taste (example: Creole seasoning, garlic salt, pepper). Put to the side when cooked thoroughly.

title: ham and broccoli corn bread bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat 1 Tbsp. of the oil in a 10 inch skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add onion.
Cook. Stir until tender.
Add ham.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes until hot.
In a large bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add milk, remaining oil, corn meal mix and corn.
Blend well.
Stir in broccoli, cheese, onion, ham mixture and hot sauce.
Pour into greased iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: hot pepper vinegar
directions: I plant plenty of hot peppers each year in my garden.
My favorites are cayenne and jalapeno.
When canning, I also can plenty of this zappy seasoning that I use on vegetable and meat dishes.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick and add margarine.
Chop apples; put in after mixture has cooled.
Stir all together.
Put in dish.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Add chopped nuts.

title: taco soup
directions: **In place of large can of tomatoes, you can substitute small can plain diced tomatoes with green chilies.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and seasoning.
Drain meat.
Brown onions and pepper.
Mix with meat in skillet.
Pour soups and a can of water. Simmer 10 minutes. Mix with noodles.
Top with grated cheese. Put in a long casserole dish.
Cover and bake about 25 minutes. Uncover about 10 minutes.
When you cook noodles, let them get tender and drain.
Set aside until the meat is ready.
Makes 6 servings.

title: three bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
This recipe may be doubled using 41 ounce cans of beans.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and green pepper.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a large casserole.
Spread 1 can of mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: baked sweet potato
directions: Cook sweet potatoes for 15 minutes on boiling temperature in saucepan.
Cook down liquid to half.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour mixture into round casserole and decorate, if desired.
Bake at 375° approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together and freeze in gallon freezer.

title: hot spinach
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add flour until blended and smooth but not brown.
Add spinach liquid and milk, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Add rest of the ingredients and combine with cooked spinach.
Put in a casserole and top with buttered crumbs.
Cook at 350° until hot.

title: club punch
directions: Boil water
and sugar.
Turn fire off and stir in jello until dissolved.
Stir in juice and lemon juice.
Let chill in freezer. Add equal amount of water.
Rechill in freezer until almost frozen.
Serve at once.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, one egg and butter. (Batter will be thick.) Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 3 eggs.
Mix with mixer.
Pour over cake mix.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Add sugar to water; bring to boil and boil 2 minutes. Dissolve orange Jell-O in hot liquid.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Pour into loaf pan.
When partially frozen, beat with rotary eggbeater until fluffy.
Add milk and blend.
Continue freezing, stirring after 20 minutes or so.
Freezes in 5 to 6 hours.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: congealed strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Mix gelatin and pineapple in large sauce pan.
Heat on stove until gelatin is dissolved, do not boil.
Allow to cool.
Mix in buttermilk, pecans, and whipped topping until blended.
Pour into an 8 x 12 inch oblong dish or clear glass bowl.
Refrigerate. Makes a beautiful light salad.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cover squash and onion with water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and cook until done.
Drain, mash and cool.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, sugar and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt margarine in small skillet and stir in corn flakes until all margarine is absorbed.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions and pour into pie crust. Slice bananas on top of pudding.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and egg yolks, beating after each.
Alternate milk and flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350°. Makes 3 layers.

title: cucumber dip
directions: As cream cheese softens, peel cucumber and remove all seeds. Using a food processor, grind cucumbers.
Drain very well.
(Make sure ground cucumber is very dry.)
Add minced onion, cream cheese and season to taste.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables or chips or use to make party sandwiches.

title: pea casserole supreme
directions: Mix ingredients and microwave on High until heated through, about 10 minutes.

title: chicken a la mexicale
directions: Mix red pepper with vegetable oil.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Stir in flour mixed with water; cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Pour into a baking dish.
Place chicken on sauce.
In another pan, combine tomatoes, green peppers and onion with chicken broth and salt to taste.
Cook until vegetables are very soft.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° to 400° until cheese melts.

title: supreme chicken casserole
directions: Mash crackers and put 1/2 box on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Combine chicken, soups and sour cream and pour in pan over crackers.
Top with rest of box of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ed's spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain thoroughly and place in casserole.
Put undiluted soup in top of double boiler and add grated cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted and well-blended.
Pour sauce over spinach and top with partially cooked bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Place under broiler to crisp bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: northa's chocolate pie
directions: Combine Crisco and 1 cup flour; sprinkle water over and make two crusts.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Set aside.

title: appetizer pinwheels
directions: Spread cream cheese on lunch meat; roll and chill.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and serve on crackers.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat the egg yolks and sugar until thick.
Add bourbon and stir thoroughly.
Add heavy cream and milk and continue whipping.
Break up the ice cream
and add to mixture.
Stir until smooth.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and fold into egg nog. Refrigerate if possible for 30 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.

title: "season's" wings
directions: Clip tips off wings if desired.
Arrange on cookie sheet. Spray lightly with Pam.
Sprinkle with dry Italian dressing.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. Turn and sprinkle with remaining dressing. Bake additional 20 minutes.
(Add a salad and you have an extra good meal.)

title: green tomato jello jelly
directions: Mix tomatoes and sugar together.
Cook 15 minutes.
Stir in Jell-O.
Put in clean, sterilized jars.
Seal.
Yields 2 pints.

title: cranberry fluff waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, nuts and salt. Fold in Cool Whip and chill.
Looks attractive served in glass bowl.

title: my favorite rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a covered casserole. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix sugar and oil with electric mixer, beating at high speed for 1 minute.
Mix dry ingredients and add dates (optional).
Add to sugar mixture.
Fold in apples, vanilla and nuts and pour into greased and flour-dusted angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Bring 2 1/4 cups cold water to boil in 2-quart saucepan.
Add potatoes; simmer, uncovered, over medium heat 15 to 18 minutes or until most of water is absorbed.
Stir in sauce mix and milk; simmer 4 to 5 minutes until sauce thickens.
Stir frequently; cool.
Stir in dressing, cheese, peppers and onions; chill.
Top with bacon.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Empty cans of beans, Chinese vegetables, mushrooms and water chestnuts in large drainer; drain well.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine, saute onions and green peppers until soft but still crisp.
Drain and add to vegetables.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix drained vegetables well in large bowl; combine soup, sour cream, salt and black pepper.
Pour over vegetables and mix.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Melt 1/3 cup margarine, stir in bread crumbs; mix well. Remove from heat and stir in grated cheese, spread evenly over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fancy pancakes
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour onto griddle and cook until golden.
To serve:
brush with little butter; serve with jam or eat alone.

title: sugar tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add a dab of the sifted dry ingredients and beat well.
Then add a dab of the milk and beat well.
Repeat this until the dry ingredients and milk are all gone.
Add nuts.
Drop by the spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar on each cookie when taken out of the oven.

title: won't last long cake
directions: Mix well eggs, oil and sugar.
Stir well flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in pineapple, bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Mix in order and pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
No frosting.
Only bake about 50 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Add lettuce, Ranch Style beans and cheese.
Slice tomatoes into chunks and add to salad.
Crush Doritos and add to salad.
Then, add Catalina salad dressing.
Mix together.
Serve.
Real good.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Make macaroni and cheese to package directions.
Mix beef, macaroni and cheese, cream of mushroom soup, onion and mushrooms in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugarless fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; chill in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: california pasta salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 1-inch pieces; cook and drain.
Combine all of the ingredients in a large bowl; cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.

title: strawberry-pear shake
directions: Combine all ingredients into electric blender. Process until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: meat balls and dunky sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into small balls.
Place in a baking pan. Cover with foil. Bake 20 minutes at 350° or 400° until done.
Remove foil and let them brown a little.

title: pudding - wiches
directions: Cook pudding.
While hot, stir in peanut butter.
Cook until thick.
Spread pudding 1/2-inch thick on vanilla wafers or graham crackers.
Top with another cookie and freeze until firm.
May be kept in freezer for anytime snack.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate or quiche dish. Parcook vegetables to almost tender and drain.
Mix broccoli, onion, pepper, cheese, salt and pepper in pie plate or quiche dish.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (1 minute with hand beater or 15 seconds in blender).
Pour into pie plate or dish. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown and knife comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just until tender.
Drain and arrange in the bottom of a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of cheese and the chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with rice. Make a white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice and sour cream.
Pour over rice.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: special coffee cake
directions: Follow recipe for Nestle Toll House chocolate chip cookies, but use Crisco instead of butter and melt it completely first along with a handful of chocolate chips (usually 1 to 2 minutes in microwave).
The cookies won't flatten out while baking.
Everyone will want to know your secret.

title: french onion soup
directions: In 5-quart pan, heat bacon drippings (shortening).
Add onion; saute over low heat until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Stir in flour and brown slightly.
Gradually add stock and salt and pepper.
Cook covered over low heat for 30 minutes.
In 6 heatproof bowls, place slice of toast; cover each with slice of cheese.
Pour soup over top.
Sprinkle each with Parmesan cheese. Run under broiler to melt cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rocky road drops
directions: Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Set aside.
In a medium heavy saucepan melt chocolate pieces and confectioners coating over low heat, stirring often.
Remove pan from heat.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together cereal, marshmallows and peanuts.
Add cereal mixture to melted chocolate, stirring until combined.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on the prepared cookie sheet.
Chill about 1 hour or until firm.
Store tightly covered in the refrigerator. Makes about 36.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Add shortening, brown sugar, eggs and soda, dissolved in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Mix , then add flour and spices.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Wash, pick and drain cranberries.
Make a bouquet of spice (wrap and tie in cheesecloth).
Cook cranberries, sugar, spice bouquet and water over moderate heat until cranberry skins pop. Add apples, pears, onion, celery and raisins.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches a light jelly like consistency (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Remove from heat; discard spice bouquet and add almonds.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 4 pints.
Excellent!

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place fruit in oblong pan.
Mix all other ingredients until crumbly by hand and crumble over fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion gently in butter until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.

title: date muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Mix baking mix, sugar, egg and water; beat for 30 seconds.
Stir in dates.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full. Bake 15 minutes.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: turkey divan
directions: Combine soup and milk in 2-quart casserole. Stir until smooth. Stir in turkey and pepper.
Cover and cook on High 7 to 9 minutes.

title: cabbage wedges
directions: Cut head of cabbage into wedges.
Cook in water until done. Drain.

title: banana foster cheesecake squares
directions: Mix crumbs, pecans, butter and sugar. Press onto bottom of a 13 x 9 inch pan.

title: warm bubbly
directions: Warm milk. Add the extract but just a little bit (more or less for flavoring).
Stir.
Warm some more until its hot enough to feel it go down.
Put in contaner.
Shake well.
Serve.
Best right before bed.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef and vegetables until they are tender; drain.
Add chili sauce, catsup, 1/2 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Simmer 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion. Combine all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Pour enough beer in ingredients to make batter the consistency of pancake batter.
This may also be used for chicken or sliced egg plant, or squash.
It makes a light, nongreasy crust.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given until dough is stiff.
Roll out thin.
Cut with cookie cutters and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: rhubarb pie(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cut rhubarb in pieces 1/4-inch thick.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, flour, tapioca, salt, lemon or orange juice and 2 egg yolks and mix together, then mix with rhubarb.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites in with the rhubarb combination.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: spanish cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon bubble bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Set aside and let rise.
Punch down.
Roll little balls in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place in loaf pan 3 deep.
Pour 2 tablespoons sweet butter or margarine over little dough balls.
Set aside and let rise until double in size.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Top with glaze if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and reserve broth.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Use broth to cook noodles.
Mix noodles and chicken with all other ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until bubbly and slightly brown.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix.
(It will get watery after awhile, so do not mix until ready to fry.)
Fry in hot skillet with vegetable oil.
Drain.

title: scampi alla "fireman chef"(makes 8 first-course servings)
directions: Rinse prawns and set aside.

Heat clarified butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook garlic 1 to 2 minutes or until softened but not brown. Add prawns, green onions, wine and lemon juice. Cook until prawns turn pink and firm, 1 to 2 minutes on each side.
Do not overcook.
Just before serving, add chopped parsley and season with salt and pepper. Serve on individual shell shaped or small gratin dishes, garnished with slice of lemon and fresh parsley sprig.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix meal, sour cream, butter and 1 tablespoon sugar and cook like cornbread, then crumble.
Mix green pepper, red pepper, onion and sweet relish with crumbled cornbread.
Mix mayonnaise and 2 tablespoons sugar; spread over top of cornbread mixture, then sprinkle cheese on top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Make up jello as directed on package.
Add 4 ice cubes to help jello set.
Add frozen strawberries.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust.
Top of pie may be decorated with strawberries.

title: rice omelet
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt and rice.
Cook in butter as a puffy omelet.

title: bret's favorite spanish shredded beef stew(ropa vieja - old clothes)
directions: Cut beef into 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat beef, water, salt, pepper and bay leaf to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer for 2 hours, until beef is tender (add water as necessary).
Remove beef from broth; pull apart into shreds.
Stir beef, onion, garlic, chiles and reserved liquid and remaining ingredients into broth.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with black beans and tortillas.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks and sour cream; set aside.
Put rhubarb in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour sour cream mixture over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Beat egg whites, sugar and cream of tartar.
Spread on top of baked pie and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: tong's egg rolls(30)
directions: Grind this all up as you would for cole slaw.
Cut onion up in small pieces.
Mix together real good.
Egg roll skins at Eberhard or Krogers.
Medium heat in deep fryer Wesson oil or Crisco 15 to 20 minutes; turn until done.
If they turn dark brown, turn heat down.
Drain on paper towel.
Can freeze them, too.

title: "aunt rosie's" corn relish
directions: In large Dutch oven, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and turmeric.
Heat to boiling.
Add the vegetables.
Cook, uncovered, 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pack in hot, scalded jars.
Seal.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Slice bananas and line an 11 x 15-inch pan with them.
Slice ice cream in 1/2-inch slices and layer on top of bananas.
Freeze until firm.
Melt 1 cup of chocolate chips and 1/2 cup of butter; add powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook until mixture is thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool chocolate mixture, then pour over ice cream. Freeze until firm (overnight).
Whip the cream until stiff. Spread over chocolate layer.
Store in freezer.
Remove about 10 minutes before serving.
This will keep for several weeks in the freezer.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in water.
Heat together pineapple juice, lemon juice and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over gelatine and let stand until partially set.
Add Cheddar cheese and pineapple.
Chill until set.
Just before serving, cube gelatine with spoon and fold in one cup Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over thinly sliced cucumbers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make your instant potatoes.
Follow directions on box (approximately 6 servings).
Make the real mashed potatoes if you prefer.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Crush noodles slightly.
Place in strainer.
Pour boiling water over noodles to soften slightly.
Drain well.
Combine noodles, cabbage, onions and olives.

title: cinnamon puffs
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon in hot fat.
Cook until brown.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.

title: mother's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the first 2 ingredients; add 4 eggs, one at a time. Mix dry ingredients together and add to other mixture, alternating the dry ingredients and buttermilk. Add vanilla and lemon juice. Mix well. Pour into a well-greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cube the meat from raw chicken breasts.
Roll in flour.
Heat 2 tablespoons shortening in skillet and brown meat well on all sides.
Add mushrooms (drained).
Remove from heat.
Add paprika and blend.
Combine onion soup, sour cream and water.
Pour over meat.
Pour into casserole; cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until cake is golden brown.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and cornmeal.
Beat the egg until light and add it to the dry ingredients with the milk and melted shortening.
Beat thoroughly and bake in moderate oven.

title: pecan catfish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 500°. Dredge fillets in bread crumbs and place fillets on broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 500° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Arrange fillets on serving dish and keep warm.

title: whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Mash, hot, cooked sweet potatoes and whip in a generous amount of butter, salt and pepper (to season) and hot milk to make them creamy.
Heap in a shallow baking dish.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the meat and onion, then drain.
Place meat and onion mix in a 9 x 9-inch square pan or a round pie pan.
Mix the tomato soup in with the meat.
Do not add water to the soup.
Add and mix a dash or a couple of dashes of the pepper, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese to the meat mixture.
Drain the green beans and place them on top of the meat.
Place the mashed potatoes on top of the beans. Sprinkle the seasoned bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 40 minutes.

title: pina colada float
directions: In a pitcher, mix pineapple juice and cream of coconut.
Stir in club soda.
Serve in glasses.
Top with a scoop of ice cream. Makes 4 (10 ounce) servings.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix together and serve.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: punch
directions: Add fresh raspberries.
You may use any flavor sherbet and fresh fruits of your choice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bone and cut chicken in about 2-inch pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of a large casserole. Top with egg slices.
Add vegetables. Spoon soup on top of vegetables.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put oven rack on bottom shelf.
Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add flour.
Mix until only pea size lumps remain (like pancake batter).
Pour into Teflon muffin tins or spray regular tins with cooking spray.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 20 minutes. Do not peek.
Remove from oven and cool in tin for a few minutes before serving.

title: fried spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into patties.
Fry in oil.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preparation Time:
30 minutes.
Cooking Time: 10 minutes. Oven Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg.
Add flavoring and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour; measure and sift with salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to creamed shortening and sugar.
Pour into well oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: sinfully rich chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and grease cookie sheets.
Mix together flour and baking soda and set aside.
In a separate bowl, beat butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar in a bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until blended.
Stir in flour mixture and blend.
Add nuts and chocolate chips and mix.
Using a tablespoon, form walnut-size balls.
Place dough 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes, until golden brown on edges and lightly brown on top of cookie.
Cool on wire racks.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Mix in spaghetti sauce.
Layer lasagna noodles (uncooked) on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 ground beef mixture on noodles.
Spread 1/2 cottage cheese on ground beef.
Spread 1/2 Mozzarella cheese on cottage cheese. Repeat.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients and pour over first 5.
Let set overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to the cooked and mashed potatoes.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, cheese and oregano.
Spoon over chicken. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crunchy cheese snacks
directions: Combine cheese, flour, cereal, bacon, salt, dry mustard, red pepper and garlic powder.
Add butter; stir with fork until blended.
Sprinkle water over and stir until dough forms a ball. By level tablespoons, drop dough onto greased baking sheet. Press a pecan half in center.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute bacon and drain; tear into pieces and put in a large pot.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Cool and put through blender until smooth.
May be frozen.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients.
Form into loaf.
Bring to boil next 4 ingredients.
Pour over raw ham loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 250°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Garnish with watercress or parsley.

title: frosted strawberry ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add vanilla ice cream, stirring until melted.
Chill until partially set.
Fold strawberries into gelatin mixture.
Pour into 6-cup ring mold and chill until firm.

title: beef dip
directions: Cut top off of bread.
Scoop out pieces of bread (finger size pieces).
Fill with sour cream mix. Pile pieces of bread loosely around loaf. Chill.
Use bread to dip.
Eat and enjoy.
Good stuff!
Great for parties and get togethers.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook brownies according to directions; let cool.
Prick holes in brownies with fork and pour liqueur over.
Prepare mousse according to directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces with food processor.
Break up 1/2 of brownies into small pieces and place in bottom of trifle.
Cover with 1/2 of mousse, 1/2 the candy, 1/2 the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, sprinkling second layer of Cool Whip with reserved crushed candy or curled chocolate.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine graham crackers and melted butter.
Press firmly into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer in slices 1/2 ice cream.
Pour 1/2 topping on ice cream.
Sprinkle 1/2 peanuts on topping.
Repeat ice cream, caramel and nut layers.
Keep frozen.
Best if chilled a few hours and eaten within a few days.
Keep covered in freezer.

title: swedish brownies
directions: Mix first six ingredients together thoroughly.
Spread batter evenly in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle almonds and cinnamon sugar on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: turkey and pepper stir-fry
directions: For sauce, in a small bowl, combine water, soy sauce and cornstarch. Set aside.

title: mexican hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken broth.
Layer chips in a baking dish.
Top with half of meat, then half of soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chili eggs
directions: Beat eggs; add chiles and cheese.
Cook in skillet.
Top with XLNT, Hormel, Stagg or your own homemade chili.

title: makai nui ripple steaks
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer.
Do not salt.
Prick with a fork.
Let stand 20 minutes.
If you need to hold longer chill in refrigerator.
Weave on a skewer around pineapple; brush with sauce.
Grill quickly over glowing coals.
Baste often.
Do not overcook.

title: cheese potato bake
directions: Peel and slice potatoes as French fries.
Cook bacon and crumble into small pieces, cut cheese into small pieces, quarter and slice onions.
Mix all ingredients, salt and pepper to taste, cut butter up in small pieces and put on top of mixture in heavy duty foil.
Close tightly, bake in 375° oven approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Use a shallow 9 x 12-inch pan or pie pan.
Spread sour cream in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over sour cream. Drizzle taco sauce over cheese.
Top with green pepper and tomato pieces.
Serve with chips, using chips as shovels dipping into sour cream mixture.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off excess fat.
Add other ingredients. Cook slow, about 30 minutes.

title: sugarless dried apple cake
directions: Cook apples.
Add raisins and nuts to the cooked apples. Combine dry ingredients and then cut in margarine.
Add this to the apple mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour batter into tube pan or coffee cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beer burgers
directions: Cut Smok-Y-Links into bite size pieces.
Put everything into skillet; cook until liquid is gone.
Smells bad, but tastes good. Is hot.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugar.
Add melted chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg at medium speed.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill several hours.
I add Cool Whip as a topping as I serve.
This pie is just as good the next day, if kept in the refrigerator.
Easy recipe.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Beat well.
Add coconut and blend well.
Fold whipped topping into mixture.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: one-step tamale pie
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic; stir in other ingredients in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in a large stock pot.
Cover with water, bouillon cubes and spices.
Peel and chop veggies.
Add to stock pot and cook until chicken is tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken and place on platter to cool.
Place veggies in a separate bowl.
After chicken is cool, debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Line each pan with crust.
Put veggies in crust with gravy and chicken. Cover with top crust and pinch edges together.
Make slits in top of crust.
Makes two 9-inch pies.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate chips.
Beat egg whites with 1 shake of salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in melted chocolate and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dill dressing
directions: Whisk vinegar and mustard in a small bowl.
Whisk in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Stir well before serving with salad.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Stir until smooth and add butter. Put in 2 unbaked pie shells and bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Use the egg whites for meringue for the pies. You may put the whites in the pie and not have a meringue topping if you like.

title: rita and winnie's squash
directions: Mash squash.
Stir in onion, soup, sour cream and carrots. Add salt and pepper.
Fold in 2/3 of stuffing mix.
Sprinkle layer of stuffing mix in a buttered casserole.
Add squash mixture. Sprinkle with stuffing mix and dot generously with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This dish freezes well before and after baking.

title: white chocolate brownie drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat first four ingredients until smooth. Add melted chocolate; mix well.
Stir in combined dry ingredients and white chocolate.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies are almost set; center should still be moist.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool 2 minutes; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: aunt jennie's gingerbread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Beat in 2 well beaten eggs (or use 1/2 cup egg substitute or 3 egg whites).

title: pig-out vegetable soup
directions: Cook until veggies are tender.

title: benjamin likes this broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain. Combine broccoli, onion, soup, mayonnaise, egg, cheese, salt and pepper and put in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar. Beat in vanilla and eggs. Sift remaining ingredients together. Add to the sugar and egg mixture; mix well. Stir in 3/4 cup M&M's. Reserve remaining for decoration on top of cookies. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Put remaining M&M's on cookie tops. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup, broth, chilies and pepper.
Set aside. Soften tortillas by dipping one tortilla at a time into hot oil. Drain tortillas on paper towel and stack.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook hen in salted water until tender.
Cool, bone and set aside.
Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Mix flour mixture with hot broth to make dough.
Makes five portions.
Roll thin.
Cut in strips and pull off pieces about 2 or 3 inches long.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.
Keep broth boiling until all dough has been added.
Add boned chicken and plenty of broth.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Stir just enough to keep from sticking.

title: skillet cookies(aka boiled chocolate cookies)
directions: In large skillet, heat to boiling the sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter, vanilla, chopped nuts and oatmeal. Stir well. (May add small amount more of oatmeal if needed.) Spoon in small mounds on waxed paper to set up. (May take 30 minutes to dry and set up.) Store in tight-lidded container.

title: banana sandwich
directions: Spread mayonnaise on both sides of bread.
Place banana bet ween both pieces of bread.
Peanut butter is optional.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well; add mashed bananas and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix to moisten flour. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese, sausage and black pepper.
Add flour and form into small balls.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, molasses and egg.
Mix in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar. Place balls, sugared sides up, about 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 7 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.

title: brunch in a dish
directions: Place hash browns in slightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer cooked sausage over hash browns.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more or until set and lightly browned.
Serves 8.

title: super nachos
directions: Fry first 3 ingredients for about 10 minutes.
Spread beans in 10 x 13-inch casserole.
Put grated cheese, chilies and taco sauce over beans.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Put guacamole, sour cream, olives and onions on top.
Put taco chips around edges, rest in bowl (about 3 bags).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and bacon in frying pan until done.
Cook rice and place in long casserole dish.
Add soup, bacon and chicken mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. The water chestnuts are optional.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg whites together with cream of tartar.
When stiff, add sugar and beat.
Fold into cooked mixture and fill baked pie shell.
Brown in 450° oven.

title: quick blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a large 9 x 9-inch dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk together.
Pour onto top of melted butter. Pour berries on top of the batter.
Dough rises through berries to make crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Prepare dough by blending flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, shortening, egg and milk.
Roll out and cut into strips. Place some chicken pieces in a casserole dish and layer with strips of dough, dotted with pieces of butter.
Make 3 layers ending with dough.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.
Serve with gravy.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread crescent rolls in bottom of pan.
Press together against sides.
Brown sausage.
Sprinkle on top of crescent.
Mix eggs and water together and pour over the mixture.
Spread cheese on top and bake for 25 minutes on 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in alternately with water.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach and bacon salad
directions: Tear spinach leaves into bite-sized pieces; place in a salad bowl.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain (reserve fat) and crumble slices.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in 2-quart saucepan. Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook to hard ball stage (260°) without stirring. Remove from heat. Stir in butter, flavoring and food coloring. Pour into buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.

Cool until comfortable to handle. Butter hands, gather taffy into ball and pull. When candy is light colored and gets hard to pull, cut into quarters. Pull each piece into long strand about 1/2 inch thick. With buttered scissors, cut quickly into bite size pieces. Wrap each piece in clear plastic wrap. Makes 1 1/4 pounds of candy.

title: twinky cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake according to instructions on cake mix box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Allow to cool.
Split into 2 layers using thread or a knife.

title: dorothy's lefse
directions: Cool potatoes, preferably overnight.
Add 1 cup flour to this mixture and divide into small portions to be rolled out.
Use a sleeve on your rolling pin.
Roll out on a pastry cloth.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown meat with onions; drain.
Mix taco seasoning with 1 cup water, then mix Ranch dressing with 1 cup water.
Mix all ingredients together in large cooker and simmer 45 minutes.
Top with nachos and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: applesauce loaf cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat with mixer on medium for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: enchilada soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil over medium high heat. Add ground meat to onions and garlic; brown. Add undiluted soups, chilies, water, steak sauce, Worcestershire sauce, cumin, chili powder, pepper, and enchilada seasoning; bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat; simmer 1 hour. Add chips and queso cheese dip. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Mix in beans and taco seasoning to hamburger; spread in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Spread sour cream and cheddar cheese over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle onions over mixture when it comes out of the oven.
Mix tomatoes and salsa in a blender and pour over mix. Serve with any kind of taco chips, best when served warm.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups cold water with Knox; set aside (cold mixture). Mix jello, boiling water and sugar in saucepan; bring just to a boil and add cold mixture.
Add 1 cup cold water; stir well and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate approximately 3 hours. Cut into blocks or use cookie cutters for fun shapes.

title: chuck wagon mac
directions: Prepare dinner as directed; brown meat.
Add celery, green pepper and onion;
cook until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, tomatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Add dinner; mix well and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently or pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together and spoon over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: beer dogs
directions: Mix ketchup and brown sugar together in a slow cooker.
Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces; add to mixture.
Bring to a high simmer.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 can of beer.
Turn slow cooker to medium heat; cook, uncovered, for 4 or more hours, until thickened.

title: quick and zesty vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, brown meat and onion.
Cook until onion is tender; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Serves 8.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended. Pour into a 9 x 9 square pan, greased and floured or double the ingredients and use a 9 1/2 x 13 pan or Bundt pan.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth. Gently stir in 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Spread on bottom of crust.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Use may use liquid from boiled lean ham as seasoning.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and add vanilla as you are beating. Add all ingredients. Continue to beat as you add ingredients. Add enough milk to finish filling freezer container. Freeze by electric or hand freezer. Top with any delicious topping.

title: peek-a-boo cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix together margarine, sugar and eggs (beat in one egg at a time).
Add vanilla, salt and flour.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread half of batter in pan; then spoon pie filling over batter.
Drop remaining batter over pie filling. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in salad bowl; toss lightly and serve. Complements any meat, but especially good with ham, pork and sausages.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased loaf pan about 1 hour at 350°.

title: rosemary-garlic yams
directions: Cut yams into 1-inch slices; cut each slice into quarters. Place in a large shallow pan; sprinkle with crushed garlic cloves. Add olive oil and remaining ingredients, stirring to coat.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender, stirring every 10 minutes.
Remove and discard garlic, if desired.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan over high heat; cook until it starts to boil, then pour over ground cabbage already in jars, then seal.

title: carrot and onion puff
directions: Bring to boiling the onion, carrots, garlic and water in a saucepan.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender (stir occasionally).
Do not drain.
Stir in milk, oat bran, parsley, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Over medium-high heat, bring to boiling; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted.
Cool slightly.
In large mixer bowl beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into vegetable mixture.
Pour into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart souffle dish and bake for 50 minutes in a 325° oven.
Top should be brown and a knife inserted near the center should come out clean.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Cut sausage lengthwise into 4 pieces.
Cut pieces into 1/2-inch slices.
Brown in a Dutch oven; drain, reserving drippings.
Set aside.
Brown chicken in drippings; drain. Combine oil and flour in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until roux is the color of chocolate (about 30 minutes).
Add minced onion and next 3 ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Add chicken, Creole seasoning and hot sauce.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: brown bag biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, allspice, cinnamon, nutmeg, and ginger in a paper bag.
Separate biscuits and cut each in half.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine over low heat and dip biscuit pieces into margarine.
Drop biscuits into paper bag and shake to coat.
Place in well greased 9-inch x 9-inch square cake pan, side by side, to make one layer.
If any margarine is left, drizzle on top.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Eat and enjoy!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix casserole ingredients and pour in dish.

title: hanna's swedish pepper cookies(pepparkakor)
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Sift dry ingredients (except baking soda).
Mix molasses and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into log approximately 2 1/2 to 3-inches in diameter.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Slice paper thin.
Put piece of almond in center.
Bake in moderate oven (350° to 375°) for 10 minutes.
Watch out.
They burn quickly.

title: marinade for beef jerky
directions: Cut strips of beef or deer meat into thin strips.
Mix marinade ingredients and cover meat.
Keep refrigerated for 24 hours.
Place meat strips in dehydrator or 200° oven until dried to desired texture.

title: spiced apple tea
directions: Combine juice, cloves and cinnamon stick in small saucepan; bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Pound steak lightly on both sides.
Spread one side with carrots mixed with bread, margarine, spices and cream.
Roll up and tie with white cord or peg with skewers.
Fit into baking pan and sprinkle with flour.
Add water and cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Baste several times with drippings.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes to brown thoroughly.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs.
Add salt, sugar, syrup, shortening, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in a partially cooked pie shell and bake at 325° about 45 minutes.
The nuts will flatten the top, forming a firm crust that will brown nicely if baked slowly.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil for 30 minutes.
Shuck corn, cut corn off; put in jars and seal.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix milk, eggs and sugar and add rice.
Mix well and add vanilla and nutmeg and mix lightly.
Place in individual casserole dishes or larger casserole dish and bake at 400° until brown on top.
Serves about 6.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in pressure cooker. Put all vegetables in a bowl. Combine tomato soup, oil, sugar, vinegar and spices in a pan. Bring to a boil; pour over vegetables. Store in refrigerator.

title: banana-chocolate malt
directions: In blender container, combine milk, banana and malted milk powder.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls; blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Rub potatoes in baking grease. Roll in coarse salt. Wrap in tinfoil. Bake 1 hour or until done. Remove from oven. Slice potatoes lengthwise (be careful, hot). Remove potatoes from the shell; careful not to break the skin. Put in a bowl along with the sour cream, mayonnaise, chopped hard-boiled eggs and half of cheese. Mix together. Put mixture back into potato shells. Add as much as you can to each potato. Top with remaining cheese. Bake in hot oven until cheese is melted and potatoes are hot at 350°.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli without salt; drain.
Saute onion in oleo until onion is clear.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat until cheese melts.
Add broccoli.
Serve warm with your favorite chips or crackers.

title: chili taco salad
directions: Brown 1 pound ground beef; pour off excess fat.
Stir in 1 envelope taco seasoning mix, 16 ounce can of tomatoes, kidney beans and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: paige's apples
directions: Peel the skin off.
Cut it up.

title: "fool"
directions: For four people, use 2 cups or more of raw, well rinsed berries, strawberries, raspberries, blackberries or a combination. Crush about 1/2 of them gently with a fork, just to set the juices running.
Add sugar to taste depending on the berries' sweetness and ripeness.
Set them aside, covered, in a cool place for at least 30 minutes to develop flavor.
Measure the crushed berries; measure an equal amount of whipping cream; beat until it holds a gently shape.
Fold berries into cream so there is a pleasing contrast of fruit and cream.
Serve in large bowl or individual sorbet cups.

title: aunt mary's spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain in sieve; press out as much liquid as possible.
In medium bowl, combine spinach, stuffing mix, cheese, eggs, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and roll into balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
After completely frozen, remove and place in freezer bag.

title: hummus
directions: Heat chickpeas; drain and blend in blender with chopped garlic. Add sesame seed oil.
Blend.
Add lemon juice and blend.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with pita bread wedges.

title: greek rice
directions: Saute onion and lettuce in the butter.
Add rice and then consomme and goya beef bouillon and cook.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and cinnamon in medium bowl. Set aside.

title: puffy omelet
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat egg whites with water and salt until stiff but not dry.
In another bowl, mix yolks with pepper until thick and lemon colored.
Fold in egg whites.
Heat oven to 325°.
Heat butter in skillet until hot and pour omelet mixture into skillet.
Cook until light and fluffy.
Place in oven and bake 12 to 15 minutes (use oven safe skillet).
Tip skillet to loosen omelet.
Fold omelet in half being careful not to break. Slip onto plate.
Serve warm.

title: spiced bacon twists
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Oven rack needs to be placed in the middle. For easy clean up, use 2 pieces of aluminum foil to line the bottom of a large broiler pan and place broiler pan rack on top or you can use a large baking sheet with sides lined with foil also.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and beaten yolks with a small amount of the water.
Mix smooth, then add remaining water. Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly. Add butter and vanilla. Let cool.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue from the egg whites and brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, water and sugar for 10 minutes.
Add 1 package Jell-O, apple, orange and nuts.
Mix well and refrigerate until set.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl, then add wet ingredients.
Mix a little.
Batter should have some lumps. Grease griddle or frying pan lightly.
Pour 1/2 cup of batter per pancake.
Turn when pancake looks bubbly.

title: jumbo oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Spoon dough into 1/3 cup and turn out onto greased cookie sheet, spacing 6-inches apart. Lightly grease bottom of a glass pie pan.
Dip into sugar and use to flatten each cookie into a 4-inch circle.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: coq au vin
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat pieces of chicken.
Melt butter and oil in a heavy skillet.
Put browned chicken in shallow baking dish.
Retain drippings.
Add Burgundy, peppercorns, parsley, thyme, bay leaves, garlic, salt pork and chopped mushrooms.
Add chopped onions.
Boil liquid for 5 to 10 minutes in skillet.
Remove salt pork.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: mama jo's chicken casserole
directions: Layer crushed Fritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer diced chicken over Fritos.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Mix.
Layer soup mixture over chicken.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put hash brown and melted oleo in 9x13 pan.
In a bowl, mix together sour cream, cream of chicken soup, grated cheddar cheese, salt, and pepper.
Combine this mixture with the potatoes.
Mix together corn flakes and melted oleo.
Place on top of potatoes. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat egg and add milk and vanilla. Add flour and baking powder.
Chill for 2 hours.
Use plenty of flour and knead dough until easy to handle (not sticky).
Roll out and cut.
Bake 8 minutes in 400° oven or until golden brown. Decorate.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap bacon slices around water chestnuts.
Arrange in baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Drain fat.

title: tater tot dinner
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frying pan.
Add soup and stir until mixed.
