Stir in vegetables and heat.
Put hamburger mixture in casserole dish and top with Tater Tots.
Place in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until Tater Tots are cooked through. Serves 6 to 8.

title: citrus sensation
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Pour into blender.
Add water, ice and sherbet.
Chill 45 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Mix onion and beef after browning separately.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Add sauce to meat mixture.
Mix noodles with meat and sauce; add beef bouillon.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Pour milk and oil into bowl.
Add flour and mix until mixture begins to cover away from side of bowl.
Be sure to add flour slowly so mixture doesn't become too stiff.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll 1/2-inch thick, cut and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes in 450° oven.
Makes approximately 24 small biscuits.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, vanilla and nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: microwave meaty macaroni
directions: Cook ground beef in microwave 4 to 5 minutes on High in a plastic colander which has been placed in a dish to catch the grease.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish except the cheese and cook on High, covered 12 to 14 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Let stand covered 4 to 6 minutes before serving.

title: apple meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pack into greased loaf pan, 8 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Cook
potatoes, onions, celery and pepper
in broth where meat was
cooked.
After
removing bones from meat, mix all ingredients in a
large	boiler	and simmer about 30 to 45 minutes, stirring often.

title: nacho sauce
directions: Mix in slow cooker.
Heat and serve over tortilla chips. "Great for a party."

title: impossible broccoli & cheddar appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 9 X 9 pan.
Mix broccoli, corn, onion and walnuts.
Place in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients except cheese until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high, stopping blender frequently to scrape sides if necessary, or 1 minute with electric mixer on high.
Pour evenly into pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (23 to 25 minutes); sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted (2 to 3 minutes longer); cool 30 minutes.
Cut into triangles or squares.
Yield: 30 appetizers.

title: pepperoni-pizza burgers(servings: 6  preparation time:  30 minutes.)
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and oregano.
In a food processor, chop onion, pepper and pepperoni.
Add to beef mixture.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Spoon onto buns; top with cheese and mushrooms.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer until rice is tender.
Lower heat and add egg yolks slowly.
Cook for a few additional minutes.
Pour into dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cream margarine and add brown sugar, flour and salt and mix together.
Peel, quarter and core apples and slice thin.
Put apples in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the white sugar on top of apples and add brown sugar mixture on top of this.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until apples are tender.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix as batter for cake.
Line pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Over hot baked bread, pour juice and remaining rind of one lemon and 1/2 cup sugar which has been cooked and cooled.

title: chocolate fudge i
directions: Melt chocolate in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add powdered sugar and milk, stirring until dissolved.
Bring to a hard boil and when candy gets to a rolling boil, time for 20 minutes or 240° on candy thermometer.
Take off heat and add butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat and add nuts.
As it begins to harden, pour into a buttered pan.
Work fast or it will harden.
Let cool. Cut into squares before totally hard.
Store in airtight container.

title: a prize cookie, mincemeat cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and frost if you like.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: mary's cheesecake
directions: Follow directions for cake mix.
In separate bowl, mix Ricotta, eggs and sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Pour cake mix in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish, then pour Ricotta mixture on top of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Fifteen minutes before cake is done, sprinkle some cinnamon-sugar on the top of cake.

title: scones
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder and sugar and cut in butter as if making pie dough.
(I use my food processor.) Beat egg into half and half or milk and add to flour mixture.
Mix barely long enough to moisten flour.
Gently press into a 9-inch circle or 8 to 9-inch round cake pan and cut into 10 to 12 pie-shaped wedges for a traditional scone.
Freeze dough until needed.
Frozen dough bakes better.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix well; freeze to slush.
Add 3 quarts of ginger ale or 7-Up.
Serves 60.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat over to 350°F.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with crackers.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut in half lengthwise.
Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Heat to boiling.
Pack cucumbers into clean canning jars.
Add 2 sprigs dill weed and 4 peppercorns to each jar.
Pour vinegar solution over cucumbers to within 1/2 inch of top. Immediately adjust covers as directed by jar manufacturer.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: baked fish divine
directions: Prepare and cook broccoli 5 minutes; place on bottom of 6 x 10-inch baking pan.
Cover with fish fillets.
Salt and pepper to taste (may add garlic powder) on the fish fillets and broccoli. Mix together the cream of mushroom and shrimp soups, Cheddar cheese and Miracle Whip.
Pour over fish.
Cover with corn flake crumbs and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: In blender, combine ingredients.
Beat until frothy.
In punch bowl, add any fruit flavored drink to taste.

title: cream of turkey soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
While waiting for broth to melt, melt butter over low heat, then sift 1/2 cup flour into butter, stirring frequently (do not brown or scorch).
Add onions.
Cook mixture for at least 5 minutes.
Slowly add 1 can of milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until desired thickness.
Add to chicken broth (may be lumpy so beat with a mixer).
Add the Watkins mix diluted with 8 ounces of water.
Add other ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Cook broccoli as directed.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans; rinse well and drain again; mix.
Add green peppers and onions to beans; mix remaining ingredients and add to bean mixture.
Mix well and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: broccoli-carrot frittata(vegetable or meatless entree)
directions: In covered 10-inch omelet pan or skillet over medium heat, cook broccoli and carrot in water until tender, 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally to break apart broccoli.
Drain well and set aside. Melt butter in pan over medium heat.
Beat together eggs, milk and seasoning.
Stir in cheese, broccoli and carrot.
Pour into pan. Cook over low to medium heat until eggs are almost set, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover and let stand 8 to 10 minutes or broil about 6-inches from heat until eggs are completely set, 3 to 4 minutes. Cut into wedges and serve from pan.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make a well in dry mixture; add oil, unbeaten egg yolks, orange juice and sweetener.
Beat with a spoon until smooth or with electric mixer for 1 minute at medium speed.

title: nutty marshmallow bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir chopped peanuts, flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and egg in large bowl.
Stir in margarine with fork until mixture is crumbly.
Press in ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes.
Spoon Marshmallow Creme over hot layer.
Let stand 1 minute; spread evenly.
Drizzle topping over Creme; sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups peanuts.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Let stand until cool, then loosen edges from side of pan with wet knife. Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch bars with wet knife.
Makes 24 bars. Another fun recipe for kids to make and eat.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour into two 8 or 9-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake at 300° for about an hour.
Quick and easy!

title: crab shelau
directions: In a large pot, saute onions and peppers in margarine until tender. Add tomato paste and enough water until consistency of spaghetti sauce. Add garlic, salt, pepper and hot sauce. Add cleaned crabs. Cook slowly until done, stirring occasionally. Makes 10 to 15 servings.

title: monte cristo sandwich
directions: Combine the milk and egg and beat until well mixed. Make a sandwich by placing the meat and cheese between the

two slices of bread. Soak the sandwich, one side at a time, in the egg mixture. Melt the butter in a frying pan over medium heat. When the bread has absorbed the egg mixture, place it in the pan and fry one side at a time until both sides are golden brown. Serve hot!

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine jello, pecans and coconut.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into strawberries.
Roll in red sugar or dry jello.
Make leaves with green frosting.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine butter and cheez whiz in sauce pan and melt over low heat.
Mix together with remaining ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy 1 dish bake
directions: Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, onion powder and 3 cups cooked, cut up meat.
Mix well, then pour into ungreased baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.

title: creole cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Gradually add buttermilk.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda to 1 cup boiling water. Gradually add to cake mixture.
Bake at 350°.
Batter will be thin.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until well heated.

title: season's best spinach dip
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter over med. heat.
Stir in sauce blend.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook stirring constantly until sauce comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, 1 min. or till thickened.
Add spinach, pimientos, cheese and dill. Heat stirring frequently till cheese is melted and sauce is well blended.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream till smooth.
Serve in bowl or in a hollowed out round bread bowl.
Makes 3 cups.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for 1 package of corned beef. Form into ball and roll in the remaining corned beef.

title: sugar-free carrot raisin salad
directions: Completely dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in raisins. Combine juice and enough ice cubes to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Add to jello; stir until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice. Stir in carrot.
Spoon into individual dishes or small serving bowl.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: red bean toss
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Drain beans.
Combine with celery, pickle, onion and cheese.
Blend seasoning with mayonnaise.
Add to bean mixture and toss lightly.
Spoon into shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with corn chips.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: sassy onion dip
directions: Crumble crisp cooked bacon.
Mix with cream cheese and a little orange peel added.
Delicious.
Serve on open-faced bread slices.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and bake in greased casserole with the lid off for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: instant russian spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Use 2 to 3 rounded teaspoonfuls to a cup of boiling water.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smoothy; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set (at least 4 hours).
Serve topped with cherry pie filling.

title: cinnamon rolls(very easy)
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together. Cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Roll out into a 12 x 18-inch rectangle. Melt butter and spread over top. Sprinkle on sugar and cinnamon. Roll up and slice about 1 1/2 to 2-inches thick. Place on cookie sheet or baking dish. Allow a little space in between each roll. Cover and let rise 2 hours or overnight. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Drizzle powdered sugar glaze over rolls after baking.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Butter 3 slices bread and cut into squares.
Put in large casserole.
Combine onions, celery, peppers, mushrooms, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.

Put over bread. Cut 3 more slices of buttered bread and put on top of vegetables. Pour beaten eggs and milk over this and refrigerate for 2 hours. Spoon mushroom soup on top and 2 more slices of buttered bread, cut into small cubes.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken into pieces in Dutch oven.
Add water until chicken pieces are covered.
Bring to boil; simmer until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from broth (saving broth).
Cool, skin and debone, shredding chicken into strips.
Bring broth back to a boil.
Add dumplings, a few at a time, returning to a boil after each addition.
After all dumplings are added, bring to a boil and simmer at medium heat for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add chicken pieces, celery salt, stick of butter and pepper to taste.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Let stand about 15 minutes (will thicken the longer it stands).
You can add 1 cup of chicken bouillon for extra flavor.
It is easy and delicious!
Serves 10.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine jello, hot water and sugar, let thicken in refrigerator.
(Let it get livery--not solid.)

title: fruit slush
directions: In a 6 quart container, combine the first seven ingredients. Cover and freeze for 12 hours, stirring every 2 hours.
May be frozen for up to 3 months.

title: manicotti
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil until golden brown.
Add beef to sauteed onion and pepper and brown well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder. Set aside.
Cream together the sugars and shortening and then add the eggs.
Beat well.
Fold in the flour mixture, oats and vanilla and then the chips and nutmeats.
Blend all together very well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 350° oven until light brown, about 10 minutes.

title: baked sauerkraut
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and cook until lightly browned.
Add drained sauerkraut and place in casserole.
Top with tomato juice.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream shortening and the sugars, then add eggs and beat.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and soda together.
Mix well, then add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Then add the oatmeal and coconut and mix.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add peanut butter and continue to beat, more slowly.
Add milk and beat until creamy.
Put in 4 quart freezer and add enough whole milk to make freezer 3/4 full.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Mix well and store in fridge overnight.
Prepare remaining ingredients.
Pour the marinated dressing over these ingredients about 2 hours before serving.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Saute chilled rice until golden (5 to 10 minutes in hot skillet).
Stir in onions, bacon, sesame seed, soy sauce, peas, carrots and sugar.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; mix all ingredients together.
Bake in loaf pan or shape into patties and fry.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Melt the cheese with the butter in medium saucepan. Add the onion. Mash the potatoes. Whip in cheese mixture and blend in the sour cream. Bake in casserole dish, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grated potato and egg gratin
directions: In pan, melt 1/2 of the butter with the oil. Add garlic and onion; fry until soft.
Transfer to a bowl. Add eggs; beat well. Stir in cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Grate the potatoes and squeeze to get out as much moisture as possible.
Pat dry with paper towels. Stir in egg mixture.
In ovenproof dish, put remaining butter. In preheated oven (400°) heat until melted and very hot.
Pour in egg and potato mixture. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm.
Serve immediately.
Sliced tomatoes are good served with this.

title: cranberry mould
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and sugar until dissolved.
Add cranberries and let stand 30 minutes, then add nuts, pineapple and strawberries.
Pour into mould and chill until set, about 4 hours.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg and mix well. Add oil and vanilla.

Mix well. Add oatmeal, coconut and nuts. Add flour, soda and salt (sifted together). Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork. Bake 12 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet a few minutes before removing.

title: chunky fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit and put in bowl.
Mix the pudding with reserved juices.
Stir over medium heat until clear and slightly thickened.
Pour over fruit and mix.

title: mint chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool to room temperature and chill thoroughly.
Garnish as desired and refrigerate leftovers.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
Alternate ingredients in greased casserole with tortillas on bottom and "wind" up with cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: oldies and youngies salad
directions: In food processor, grind up roast beef.
Toss with other ingredients.
Easy to chew for youngies or oldies.

title: grilled cheese with a twist
directions: Butter 2 slices of bread on one side.
Place onion and tomato in between cheese.
Bread with butter side out and grill as you would a regular grilled cheese sandwich.
You can add Thousand Island or Ranch dressing, if desired.

title: candy canes
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together and pour into two greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost cake.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen small cookies.

title: super fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in a heavy 2 1/2 or 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, until candy thermometer reaches 234°.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well until blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: green and white casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until clear; do not brown.
Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
I use 1/2 stick of oleo and add a little milk or water to soup.
Don't need all that fat.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon and drain on a paper towel.
Reserve drippings which onions are sauteed in.
Blend in flour, salt, sugar and celery salt.
Cook until it bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar; boil for 1 minute.
Stir in potatoes and bacon pieces.
Remove from heat and let stand until ready to serve.

title: skor cake(skor candy bars)
directions: Bake a sheet cake with devil's food cake mix.
Pierce the top with a fork.
Pour condensed milk and caramel topping (mixed together) over the top.
Crush Skor candy bars and sprinkle over the topping.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave roasted pecans
directions: Cook in microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir and cook 3 more minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Cream together the sour cream, mayonnaise and onion, then combine with rest of ingredients.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add melted and cooled oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar. Stir well.
Add melted butter, flour, milk, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook 25 minutes at 325° or until golden brown.

title: pecan pick-ups
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Divide into 24 balls.
Press into miniature greased muffin tin to form pastry crust.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Fill cups and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 24.

title: chicken breast in lemon sauce
directions: Cut each chicken breast horizontally to make 2 thin slices. Coat with flour.
Heat margarine in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken and garlic in margarine 4 to 6 minutes, turning once, until chicken is brown.
Add wine and lemon juice, sprinkle with pepper.
Heat until hot.
Serves 4.

title: good punch
directions: Mix together in large container.
Two times makes more than enough for 50 people.

title: easy cheesecake bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine and put into 9 x 13 pan. Beat cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar until creamy and pour over first layer.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: venison spareribs
directions: Split ribs and put in roasting pan.
Combine all ingredients and cover ribs with mixture.
Cover ribs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.
Turn ribs during last 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef quickly in hot oil in skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion; saute about 5 minutes.
Add broth, Worcestershire sauce and paprika.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream, catsup and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in uncovered double boiler.
Add peanut butter.
Stir.
Put peanuts, marshmallows and rice krispies in a large bowl.
Pour bark mixture over dry ingredients.
Mix. Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Let set.
(Push them together a little bit after they are dropped on wax paper.)

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts and raisins.
Cream sugar with mayonnaise until smooth.
Add soda to boiling water and mix with dry ingredients and mayonnaise.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with icing of your choice (sour cream icing is good).

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 to 3 inches vegetable oil in deep fryer or large sauce pan to 350°. Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt in medium mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Drop batter by tablespoons into hot vegetable oil. Fry a few at a time, 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Repeat with remaining batter. Serve immediately or keep warm at 175° oven. Makes about one dozen hush puppies.

title: butter brickle bars
directions: Mix
together
the cake mix (dry), butter and egg.
Pat into a jelly roll pan.
Pour the condensed milk over the base. Sprinkle the
butter
brickle
chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chop suey(serves 100)
directions: *Add extra water chestnuts and bamboo shoots, as desired.

title: quick chicken rice casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole.
Pour dry rice mix mixed with other ingredients over the chicken breasts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles(diabetic)
directions: Slice cucumbers as thin as possible.
Chop onions and pepper. Combine with the cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain cucumbers.
Combine vinegar, sweetener and spices in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Pack while hot into sterilized jars and seal at once.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown hamburg with chopped onion.
Add brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Then add tomato sauce and cook about 1/2 hour.

title: pastry for two crusts
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Sprinkle water into flour-shortening mixture a little at a time.
Mix dough thoroughly until it cleans the sides of the bowl.

Gather the dough together with your hands and press firmly into a ball. Divide dough in half and roll out on lightly floured surface. Roll from center out to form circle 1-inch larger than pie pan. Fold in half to transfer to pan easier.
Unfold.
Fill with filling; moisten rim.
Top with top crust and flute edges.
If a shell only is needed, after putting bottom crust in pan, flute edges; prick bottom crust and bake at 425° until lightly brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, reserve the broth; debone and cut chicken into shreads.
Add about 1 cup of the broth from the cooked chicken, both cans of soup, salt and pepper.
Stir and mix all together. Cover with bread crumbs.
Cook on 425° for 45 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add egg and molasses; beat thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with water, beating after each addition.

title: hot picante sauce
directions: Place onion and garlic in food processor.
Blend.
Add peppers and tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cut up strawberry into small pieces.
Pour 1 cup sugar over them; let set over night in refrigerator.
Drain juice out of berry; save the juice.
Fix cake mix as direction, except put the juice in place of water.
If not enough juice, add water.
Bake and cool; punch holes on top of cake.
Pour strawberry on top; add glaze and cool whip.
Let stand in refrigerator about one hour.

title: ham ball
directions: Ground up ham.
Set aside.
Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Chop up green onion (small).
Add green onions, seasoned salt, Worcestershire sauce and 1/4 of ham to soften cream cheese.
Mix all of this up with mixer or hands real good.
Make a ball; roll this in the rest of ham.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over hot not boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; blend in condensed milk and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Let stand at room temperature 2 hours.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in a covered container for several hours in the refrigerator.
Serve in small bowls, since it is too juicy for plates.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: almond chicken casserole
directions: To 9 cups boiling water (or water and chicken broth), add soup mix.
Boil 9 minutes.
Add rice and boil 9 minutes more.
Brown sausage and drain grease.
Add celery, onions and green pepper and saute a little.
Add to rice mixture.
Add salt, pepper and mushroom soup; blend.
Add chicken.
Place in large casserole and sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°, covered, and 15 additional minutes, uncovered.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs (beat well).
Stir together dry ingredients, gradually add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add milk and dry ingredients.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add fruit.
Bake at 250° until done.
Do not overcook.
Makes 3 layers.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut tenderloins in 1/4-inch strips.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil.
Push meat to one section of skillet.
Stir in beef broth, sugar and soy sauce.
Place the onions, bamboo shoots, water chestnuts and bean sprouts in separate sections of skillet. Cover; simmer about 20 minutes.
Never stir.
Serve over rice.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Slice all veggies thin.
Put aside for a few minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix molasses and shortening.
Put on stove and just bring to a boil, then cool.
Add rest of ingredients except 4 1/2 cups of flour.
Blend, then add flour.
Roll out on board and cut.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit dessert
directions: In 7 x 11-inch baking dish, melt 3/4 stick oleo.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk in mixing bowl (makes a thin batter).
Pour batter over melted butter.
Add fruit (do not stir into batter) over the top evenly.

title: touchdown taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef. Set aside. Spread bean dip over bottom of baking pan. Add ground beef. In mixing bowl, combine soft cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Press garlic over mixture and mix well. Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over bean and beef dip. Grate Cheddar cheese over top and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Let cool for 10 minutes. Sprinkle tomatoes, green onions, black olives and cilantro over top. Garnish with additional sour cream, if desired. Serve with tortilla chips. Party favorite. Enjoy!

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and place in a buttered casserole dish.
Beat cream and eggs together and pour over eggplant mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1- 1 1/4 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Grate sharp cheese.
Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator and let cool.
Take out and form into balls (one large or two or three small ones).
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: tinfoil meal
directions: Form a hamburger patty.
Put the hamburger patty in the center of the foil.
Put the chopped vegetables on and around the hamburger patty.
Fold the edges of the foil over the food.
Place foil, folded side up, in a preheated 450° oven for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato dish
directions: Blend sugar and egg; add milk, margarine and vanilla (or a few drops of orange flavoring is good, also; a little cinnamon if you like).
Stir in pineapple, coconut and potatoes.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie plate or small casserole dish.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon squares(these lemon squares are made in two layers)
directions: Mix all together into a dough.
Pat it out into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: creamed green beans and mushrooms
directions: Cook beans in boiling water for 15 minutes, or until tender. Drain.
Brown mushrooms in butter in a saucepan.
Add soup, cream, lemon juice and beans.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Place in a serving dish and garnish with almonds.

title: clam dip
directions: Stir cream cheese until it's of smooth consistency.
Add all other ingredients and stir thoroughly until well combined.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve with ridged potato chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together; press into a 9 x 12-inch pan (greased with oleo).
Melt chocolate chips and pour on top. Refrigerate (no cooking required).

title: sweet potato spice cake
directions: Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl. Beat in sugars and oil. Stir in potatoes and vanilla. Stir in all remaining ingredients until smooth. Lightly oil a fluted cake pan. Sprinkle with sugar; remove excess. Pour batter into pan. Cook at 325° to 350° until done.

title: chocolate coconut macaroons(30 cookies)
directions: Divide oven into thirds and preheat to 325°.
Line two cookie sheets with aluminum foil.
Break up sweet chocolate.
Place both chocolates in top of a double boiler over hot water on moderate heat.
Stir until completely melted and smooth.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool to room temperature.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Cover; let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Add soup and sauce; mix.
Sprinkle onion rings over top.
Cover casserole and place in 350° oven until warmed through, about 15 minutes.

title: sirloin steak oreganato
directions: Grate, peel and squeeze lemon juice in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Mix lemon peel, lemon juice, garlic, olive oil, salt, oregano and pepper.
Place steak in baking dish, turning to coat each side with mixture.
Preheat broiler if manufacturer directs. Place steak on rack in broiling pan.
Broil steak 12 to 15 minutes for rare or until of desired doneness, turning steak once and brushing with any remaining marinade right after turning. Thinly slice steak to serve.
Spoon any juices over slices. Garnish with fresh oregano.

title: homemade dried noodles
directions: Combine egg, milk and salt.
Add enough sifted all-purpose flour to make stiff dough (about 1 cup).
Roll very thin on floured surface; let stand for 20 minutes.
Roll up loosely; slice 1/4-inch wide.
Unroll, spread out and let dry 2 hours.
(If desired, store in container until needed.)

title: chicken salad in melon rings
directions: In medium bowl, pour lemon juice over chicken.
Add celery, onion, salt, pepper, pimentos, almonds, mayonnaise and 1 cup grapes; toss.
Cover and chill.

title: thin and tasty barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Divide sauce into separate containers for basting and serving at the table.
(Basting brushes used on raw food should not be dipped into table sauce.)
Use as a basting sauce during last 10 minutes of cooking time for burgers, chicken or ribs.
Refrigerate leftover table sauce; discard any remaining basting sauce.
Yields 2 2/3 cups.

title: chicken or beef fajitas
directions: Slice peppers, onions, beef or chicken into strips.
Saute peppers, onions and meat together until tender.
Add fajita sauce and 2 to 3 teaspoons water and simmer until meat is done.
Serve on flour tortillas.
Top with sour cream and cheese.

title: fried rice
directions: Lay bacon slices over heating base of wok.
Turn heat control to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp, about 6 minutes.
Remove bacon. Drain on paper towel and crumble.
Stir-fry onion 2 minutes in bacon drippings.
Add cold rice and stir-fry for 7 to 8 minutes. Add soy sauce, water and bacon.
Reduce heat to 250°.
Clear wok base by moving rice up along sides.
Pour eggs on base of wok. Stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until eggs are cooked.
Break in pieces; mix in rice.
Reduce heat to warm 200° for serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in confectioners sugar.
Add chopped nuts and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix and chill.
Drain cherries.
Make dough balls from mixture.
Place one cherry inside each ball. Chill again.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Roll candy balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix crumbs with sugar, pour melted butter over mixture and toss lightly.
Pat firmly over entire bottom of a 9-inch pan.

title: nut bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar thoroughly; add sour milk and beat well. Add flour sifted with salt, baking powder and soda.
Stir in nuts. Bake in waxed paper-lined 5 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch loaf pan in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour. Texture and flavor improves after 12 hours. This is excellent for nut bread sandwiches.

title: parmesan potato sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray

13X9 inch dish with Pam. In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs, parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Mix well and set aside. Peel potatoes and cut lengthwise into quarters; cut each quarter lengthwise into 3 strips. Wash strips in colander. Dip each strip in the melted butter, then in the parmesan mixture. Coat completely. Place in a single layer in baking dish. Pour any remaining butter over potatoes. Bake 30-35 minutes or until tender, turning once or twice.

title: gold peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Combine peaches, lemon juice, sugar, flour and salt in large bowl. Mix thoroughly until peaches are coated. Spoon into unbaked pie shell. Dot with butter. Moisten pastry edge with water. Cover with crust. Fold top edge under bottom crust. Flute with fingers or fork. Cut slits in top for steam to escape. Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers as small as possible.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Add milk and vanilla wafer crumbs.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Delicious!

title: apple brownies
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and egg.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add apples and nuts. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 40 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled and baked in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add 5 minutes to baking time. Consistency will vary due to difference in moisture of apples.

title: lemon-dill sauce
directions: In a
small
bowl, mix all of the ingredients, stirring well. Brush sauce
on one side of meat 1 minute before taking off the grill.
Pass
rest
of
sauce.
Makes
1/2 cup sauce. This sauce is
great
on
pork chops or just about any grilled meat.

title: tomato marinated
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients.
Mix all together and let set overnight.
Holds for several days in refrigerator.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl and then form into balls. Fry until done; drain off excess grease.

title: crabmeat mix
directions: Marinate crabmeat in lemon juice.
Cover and refrigerate for one hour.
Mix: heavy cream, mayo, cream cheese, onion, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain crabmeat and add to mix.
Spread on cocktail rye breads and broil a few minutes.
Serve.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and water together well; then stir in frosting mix and semi-sweet chocolate bits.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.

title: barbecue beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in beans, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Cut biscuits in half.

title: bavarian lunch
directions: On each of four slices of bread, layer one-fourth of beef, salad dressing and cabbage.
Top with another slice of rye.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Add drained flaked crab and mix well.
Spread on split English muffins and put under broiler until cheese starts to broil.
Remove and cut into fours and serve immediately.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and top with cheese.
Bake in a covered dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread rolls or dough (sweeter option) onto a round pizza pan, pressing all seams in dough together.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned.
Cool crust.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Make stuffing by mixing bread cubes, melted butter, sage, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup broth.
Place bread mixture over chicken.
Make gravy by thickening 1 quart broth with flour (make flour into paste before adding to broth). Stir over heat until thickened.
Pour gravy over chicken and bread.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet scrabble mix
directions: In a saucepan, heat margarine, syrup and brown sugar just until margarine is melted.
Pour over cereal and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread thin on wax paper and let cool.
Break apart.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 to 10 minutes before stirring.
Add 2 cups flour and all other ingredients with electric mixer.
Blend at low speed then beat 2 minutes.
Mix in other 2 cups flour by hand.
Cover and let stand until double. Takes 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir batter down to deflate.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise again.
Brush tops with oil.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
When done, remove chicken from the broth and separate chicken meat from the bone.
Butter Pyrex baking dish.
Roll biscuits out, then line the baking dish with biscuits.
Next, put a layer of chicken, then cut the butter into pieces and lay on top of chicken.
Repeat this process.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until done.
Prepare fettucine noodles.
Place noodles in casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of noodles.
Pour spaghetti sauce on top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook in oven until cheese is melted.

title: fried okra
directions: Slice okra; dip in egg.
Coat well with cornmeal.
In frypan, melt fat over medium heat and fry okra until well browned and crisp.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie crusts.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini noodles, drain and cool.
Cut up artichoke hearts into 1/2-inch cubes and slices.
Chop onion.
Slice olives.
Mix noodles, artichoke hearts, onions and olives and toss to mix well. Pour in the bottle of Italian with cheese dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: russian salad
directions: Boil potatoes in peeling; cool, peel, then cut in small cubes. Cook peas and carrots; hard-boil eggs and chop.
Mix carrots, peas, eggs and potatoes; drain tuna.
Flake and add to potato and vegetables.
Cut olives in half; add to salad.
Mix all with mayonnaise.
Salt to taste.

title: chunky veggie dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let sit for 2 hours.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
These freeze very well.

title: macaroni chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Mix soups, cheese, broth, chicken and macaroni.
Salt and pepper.
If you make the day before and refrigerate overnight no need to cook the macaroni.
If you bake it right away when you mix then you need to cook macaroni.
Place in a sprayed 13 X 9 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and let set for 10-15 minutes before serving.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients together; blend well.
Add a heaping tablespoonful of bacon drippings.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine and stir.
Melt margarine in skillet. Roll out batter and cut like biscuits.
Fold in half moons and place in skillet of butter.
Let rise in skillet for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Quick, easy and delicious.

title: chicken honey
directions: Mix ingredients and baste inside and outside chicken.
Wrap in foil and bake at 325° until brown.

title: sinful potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 325°.

title: seven-layer dip
directions: In a bundt pan, spray with Pam, then layer olives, cheddar cheese, onion, tomatoes.
Mix together mayo, cream cheese, and taco sauce.
This is your next layer.
Then mix avocados and lemon juice, spread on next (easy to spread with fork).
Then your last layer of bean dip, also spread with fork.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 8 hrs.
Sit bottom on pan in hot water for a few minutes then dump into platter.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and butter; mix until fine crumbs form.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans over crust.
Drizzle toffee topping evenly over top.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until topping is bubbly and golden.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top; press gently onto surface.
Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour in 350° oven. (Mine never need to bake this long.)

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat with mixer for 2 to 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Use frosting of your choice.
Seven Minute or Butter Icing are very good.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Boil ribs, chicken wings and soup bone in enough water to cover meat (approximately 20 to 25 minutes). Add all the other ingredients except the potatoes and simmer 2 to 3 hours or put in crock-pot on low for several hours. Add the potatoes several minutes before serving and keep simmering until potatoes are done.

title: creamy cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill in refrigerator.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan and heat first 3 ingredients.
When mixture starts to boil, cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add quick oats, vanilla, cocoa and coconut and/or nuts.
Mix well; then drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.
Brett's favorite.

title: macabeef microwave dish
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, cook beef for 5 minutes, until no longer pink.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes, or until hot, stirring after 5 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, let the first three ingredients dissolve. Melt 1 stick of margarine, then pour it into your saucepan. Slowly bring to a boil and let it boil for 6 minutes stirring constantly.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off oil.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer until thick.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: hamentashen cookies
directions: Beat sugar with margarine until light and fluffy.
Blend in honey, vanilla and eggs.
In a small bowl, mix flours, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add to honey mixture and stir until well blended.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight (3 hours works fine).
All or part of dough can be frozen for later use.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out dough on well floured surface.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch circles.
Put 2 teaspoons of filling in the center of the circle, fold 3 sides toward the center and pinch the edges touching together to form a triangle, like a three cornered hat.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for about 15 minutes or until dough is lightly browned.
Yields about 2 dozen hamentashen.

title: rolled fillets of flounder with lemony broccoli
directions: In a small bowl, combine butter, lemon juice, pepper and paprika; set aside.
In a larger bowl, mix rice, cheese, broccoli and 2 tablespoons of lemon butter.
On a large sheet of wax paper, lay fillets flat.
Divide rice stuffing equally and place on wide end of fillet.
Roll up; place, seam side down, in shallow baking pan coated with lemon butter.
Pour rest of sauce over fish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Follow directions on box for cake mix.
Pour 1/2 batter in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until done (about 15 minutes).
Melt caramels, butter and milk on low heat and pour over hot cake batter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Pour rest of cake batter on top.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: fruit dip
directions: With an electric mixer, blend until smooth.

title: quick crab bisque
directions: Heat soup and cream together just until hot.
Add sherry and crab meat, stirring gently.
Bring back to hot temperature.
Serve with a dollop of sour cream and sprinkle of chives.

title: "old banana" cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed, adding bananas last.
Grease and flour pan and bake at 350°.
For a 9-inch square pan, bake 25 minutes; for a 9 x 4-inch loaf pan, bake 35 to 45 minutes; for two 8 x 3-inch loaf pans, bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Use a toothpick to check cake to see if it is done.
Times are approximate.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Blend in blender the Cheddar cheese, onion and jalapeno peppers (use water). Mix the rest of the ingredients.
Brown the ground meat.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour half of the cornbread mixture in pan.
Put meat, then cheese-onion mixture, then add rest of cornbread mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: water chestnut dip
directions: Mix the ingredients and chill.
Best served with potato chips.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl. (I do mine in Kitchen Aid mixer.) Probably could use food processor. I have used my hands, but it is hard to mix. Get thoroughly mixed; roll into 1-inch balls; place on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: blueberries in heaven
directions: Crust:
Mix
flour, margarine and pecans until crumbly. Pack into
a 10 x 6-inch glass dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; let cool completely.

title: texas cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add other ingredients; mix well. Add a few shakes of garlic salt and heat.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Work together well. Form in small balls and arrange them on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°; drain on paper towels.

title: sugar and cinnamon coated pecans
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat egg white and water on high speed for 2 minutes.
Put pecans into egg white and stir until mixture is gone and pecans are well coated.
Gradually put pecans in sugar mixture until all are coated.
Place on a large greased cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, turning nuts every 15 minutes with spatula.

title: california casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add onion, green pepper, oregano and salt. Saute until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.

Layer 1/2 of the chips, 1/2 Jack cheese and 1/2 turkey in 2 1/2-quart casserole; spoon on half the sauce. Repeat layers, ending with sauce. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Spoon sour cream over top. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Continue baking 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together and bake until golden brown.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken well and dry completely.
Combine preceding mixture except butter.
Melt butter in skillet.
Dip each chicken part in butter and roll in crumb-cheese mixture.
Put in shallow pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix applesauce with allspice and place in pie crusts.
For topping, mix brown sugar, flour, margarine and cinnamon until crumbly.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Reduce to 300° and bake until topping is bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: antipasto salad(from the  simply italian recipe book)
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
In a small bowl, whisk together the oil, vinegar, sugar and seasonings.
In a large bowl, combine pasta, dressing and remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fruit toss(lo-cal)
directions: Drain pineapple; set juice aside. In a bowl, combine pineapple, mandarin oranges, strawberries, bananas and kiwi. In a small bowl, combine pineapple juice, lemon or lime juice and grated peel. Pour over fruit and toss gently to coat.

title: bonnie's bran muffins
directions: Pour water over oats.
Add melted margarine, vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Stir together flour, bran, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to oat mixture.
Blend in raisins.
Pour into muffin tins lined with muffin paper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pink popcorn balls
directions: In the bottom part of double boiler, heat about 1-inch of water to boiling.
Place the top part into bottom and put all ingredients except popcorn into pan.
Tint the syrup with a few drops of red food coloring.
Pour the melted marshmallow mixture over popped corn and shape quickly into balls with well-greased hands.
Yields 10 medium balls.

title: good and simple soup
directions: Empty stew into large dutch oven.
Remove any excess fat while emptying from can.
Cut large pieces of beef and vegetables into smaller sizes.
Add corn, butter beans, tomatoes, and remainder of seasoning (mash before adding).
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 30 - 40 minutes.
This recipe can be frozen.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, taco seasoning mix and Tabasco sauce together until smooth.
Spread on platter; leave 1/2 inch thickness.
Layer remaining ingredients in order.

title: cheese twists
directions: Cut first 5 ingredients together.
Add water.
Roll out; cut in strips and twist.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: grandmomma's chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter, sugar and vinegar over low heat.
Allow to boil for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring continuously. Remove from stove and let cool.
In a separate bowl beat eggs well. Add to above mixture.
Beat in meal and vanilla.
Place in uncooked pie crust.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix the flour, salt and cocoa into egg mixture well.
Combine soda and water and add last.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together in large mixing bowl for 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Take out of pan by turning over onto a plate.

title: "nicole's tacos"
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain grease.
Add soup, 1/2 cup water and taco seasoning.
Heat until mixture is thick.
Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons meat mixture in center of flour tortilla and roll. Place each taco in a row, in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and place in microwave or 400° preheated oven, until cheese is melted.

title: ground beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add ground beef and brown.
Cut cabbage into 1-inch squares and add to beef mixture.
Cover and cook slowly until cabbage becomes translucent, about 10 minutes. Add sour cream and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Good reheated for second day.

title: good time chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add remaining ingredients. Cook until heated through. Let simmer for another 20 minutes on low heat. Serve topped with grated cheese.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, water, butter and cinnamon in medium saucepan.
Heat to a boil, then set aside.

title: cheesy pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: apple crunch
directions: May use fruit filling of choice, except for cherries.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cool 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box. Pour half of mix into 10 x 13-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Yields 2 layers.

title: coconut or vanilla cream pie
directions: In double boiler pan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually add milk, mixing well. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils. Cook 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat; stir small amount of hot mixture into 3 slightly beaten egg yolks. Immediately remove to hot mixture. Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Pour into cooled, baked 9-inch pie shell. For coconut pie, put 3/4 can coconut in mixture and mix well. Leave out coconut for vanilla cream.
Spread meringue on top. Add coconut and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pappy bread
directions: Mix well.
If too thick, pour more water in.
It should be like pancake mix.
Pour in greased long pan and cook on 325° for 30 minutes, then turn boiler on to brown top.
Cut in squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Shape into small balls.
Press down with fork, first one way and then the other to form squares on top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place a layer of finely shredded cabbage in a casserole and season with salt, pepper and butter.
Cover
with
a layer of cracker crumbs.
Continue until casserole
is full.
Finish with a layer of crumbs. Cover with milk which
has
been
preheated. Bake 1 1/2 hours in a slow oven.

title: polish torte
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until shiny and will not pour from bowl.
Add egg yolks gradually or all at once to beaten egg whites, mixing constantly.
Add flour slowly.
Add baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in greased spring-form pan.
Check after 30 minutes.
When cool, cut in 3 or 4 layers.
Cool and set aside, then add vodka to taste.

title: green bean stir fry
directions: In a wok, stir fry chicken in the oil until fully cooked.
Add green bean stir fry and water, cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add prepared stir fry sauce or the homemade mustard sauce:
Dissolve bouillon in water and blend in remaining ingredients.
After adding either sauce heat through.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: sour cream cake
directions: I double and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix ingredients well and freeze overnight in a Pyrex dish or molds.
Serves 6.

title: cuban picadillo
directions: Fry onions and garlic in fat until soft.
Add tomatoes and bay leaf and allow to simmer a little.
Throw in meat and fry until brown, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients, stir-frying all the time.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Brown bacon in a wok.
Set heat control to medium high.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; place on paper towel, then crumble bacon.
With bacon drippings in wok, stir-fry onion for 2 minutes.

title: large carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, cinnamon and oil.
Mix well. Add carrots and pecans; mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased tube pan.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: crunchy peanut butter pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and peanut butter, beating until well blended. Gradually stir in milk.
Fold whipped topping in.

title: banana berry shake
directions: Do not allow berries to thaw.
Put all ingredients in a blender and blend for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Serves 2.

title: apricot delight
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese; mix well.
Stir occasionally until mixture begins to set.

title: layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts together.
Spread on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool; mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup of whipped topping. Spread over crust.
Spoon pudding on top of cream mixture (prepared as per directions).
Top with remaining whipped topping. Chill.
Serves 8.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: For family size, use 1/2 these amounts.

title: peanut butter confections
directions: Melt butter.
Mix together in mixer or by hand peanut butter, sugar, crumbs, melted butter and vanilla.
Drop into confectioners sugar in 2-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake or boil chicken and debone, then cut into small pieces. Cook stuffing according to directions on package.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put stuffing on top and bake for one hour at 350°.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add soda, dissolved in a little warm water, last. Bake at 350°.
Frost with caramel icing with chopped pecans.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit; place in casserole.
Combine butter, sugar and curry and spoon over fruit.
Bake at 325° one hour, covered. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, bake at 350° for 30 minutes; uncover and serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat across the grain into 1/2-inch strips, about 1 1/2 inches long.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion; cook and stir until onion is tender, then remove from skillet.
In same skillet, cook meat until light brown.
Reserving 1/3 cup of the broth, stir in remaining broth, ketchup, garlic and salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend reserved broth and flour; stir into meat mixture.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Reduce heat.
Stir in sour cream; heat.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: party dessert
directions: Mix.
When thick, pour over cream cheese mixture.

title: crab supper pie
directions: Sprinkle cheese over bottom of pie shell.
Top with crabmeat, sprinkle with green onions.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, lemon peel, mustard and mace.
Pour over crabmeat.
Top with sliced almonds.
Bake in slow (325°) oven about 45 minutes or until set. Remove from oven and let set 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bertha's casserole
directions: Mix all together and top with crushed cheese crackers and butter.
Bake till golden brown. 350° about 40 minutes.
Can be doubled for a large group.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, water, milk, margarine, salad dressing and beaten eggs.
Add chicken.
Place this in a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread the cream of chicken soup over the top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, butter and vanilla in the blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: white chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock pot on high for 3 - 4 hours.

title: cabbage rolls(microwave)
directions: Remove core and blemished cabbage leaves.
Place cabbage in large microwave casserole.
Add some water.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High (max power) 6 minutes or less until outer leaves are softened.
Separate leaves and remove and re-cook cabbage until desired amount is done.
Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce thoroughly.
Place mixture onto 6 to 8 large cabbage leaves and wrap tightly.
Line bottom of large casserole with leftover cabbage.
Place cabbage rolls on top.
Dot with butter and cover with tomato sauce.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar,	water
and Karo syrup in a heavy, large saucepan and boil to the hard-ball stage.
Check either by the cold water	method	or
use
a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add raw peanuts and salt.
Mixture will be quite thick. Return to fire
and
boil
to
golden brown and the nuts smell done.
Take from the fire.	Add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour out on	a
buttered
pan.
When
thoroughly cooled, crack into pieces and serve.

title: crepes marquis
directions: Combine eggs, flour, salt and milk; beat until smooth.
Let stand 30 minutes.
For each crepe, pour 1/4 cup batter onto hot, lightly greased skillet.
Cook on one side only.
Heat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Crumble bacon.
Cook onion and green pepper in fat until tender.
Add bacon, mushrooms and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Mix lightly.

title: leftover pinto beans
directions: "This is my favorite midnight snack."

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 326° about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: praline cookies(microwave)
directions: Break 8 crackers in half and place 4 halves across and 4 down in 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle the chopped nuts evenly over the crackers.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with raw vegetables.

title: apple crisp
directions: Bake at 350° in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
First, blend eggs, oil and vanilla until foamy.
In a separate bowl, mix cinnamon, salt, baking soda, sugar and flour with apples.
Mix the foamy mixture and the apple mixture together (the batter will be similar to cookie dough).
Bake 45 to 60 minutes, depending on whether you use glass or metal pan.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Put in the strawberries.
Let harden completely.
Then mix in whipped cream.
Break up the angel food cake into a 10-inch size pan.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Grill chicken with vegetables; add soy sauce, salt and pepper. Serve over a bed of wild rice.

title: kotta riganati(chicken with oregano)
directions: Rub all surfaces of the chicken with olive oil, lemon juice and salt mixture.
Place in a large roasting pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Melt butter.
Add tomatoes, pepper, oregano and salt to taste.
Cook over medium heat in a saucepan for 5 minutes. Pour over chickens.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake chickens for an additional 20 to 30 minutes.
Baste frequently.
Serve with rice or couscous.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: biscuits for strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl. Cut in shortening until like coarse crumbs. Make a well. Add milk all at once. Stir quickly with fork just until dough follows fork around bowl. Turn onto lightly floured surface. Knead gently for 10 to 12 strokes. Roll or pat dough until 1/2-inch thick. Dip 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter in flour; cut dough straight down. Bake at 450° on ungreased baking sheet for 12 minutes. Makes 10. Top with strawberries.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except raisins, in the top of the double boiler.
Cook, covered, for 30 minutes, or until rice is tender and milk is almost absorbed, still stirring often.

title: megan's chocolate kiss candy
directions: Unwrap candy and mix with marshmallow cream.
Mix sugar, margarine and evaporated milk; bring to a boil.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Pour over Kisses and marshmallow cream.
Mix well with mixer.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let cool completely.
Makes about 100 pieces.

title: cajun pinto beans(single dish meal)
directions: Sort and wash pinto beans.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil; turn off heat.
Let soak 1 hour.
Add hamburger meat (raw) to beans; cook over medium heat.
Add all other seasonings to taste.
Cook until beans are soft.
Serve with sliced onions and cornbread.

title: butter ball chiffons
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts.
Mix thoroughly and add the nuts last.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes. While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: cola cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add butter and cola and bring to boil.
Add to dry mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and marshmallows.
It will be a thin batter.
Bake in an ungreased and floured large oblong pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: In bowl, add flour, salt, cocoa, sugar and baking soda; blend together.
In separate bowl, mix cold water, oil, vanilla and vinegar.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix together by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all together and put in small casserole.
Bake at 350° until cheese is "gooey", 20 to 25 minutes.
Keep hot to serve with crackers.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in half.
Wash, drain, core and shred.
Melt butter or margarine in kettle over low heat.
Add shredded cabbage and saute 5 minutes.
Add sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Toss until mixed.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into dish.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: buttermilk gelatin
directions: Boil pineapple and Jell-O.
Let cool until semi-congealed. Add Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Chill and serve.

title: apple dibble dabble cake
directions: Combine vegetable oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add apple, walnuts and raisins.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven. Can be frozen.

title: duck breast broiled
directions: Sprinkle seasoning on duck.
Mix rest of ingredients, except bacon.
Marinate duck for 8 hours.
Drain and wrap duck in 3 slices bacon each piece.
Broil about 7 minutes each side.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat fruit cocktail with juice to boiling.
Add jello and mix well.
Refrigerate until it begins to congeal.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix well
and refrigerate.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Use in blender only.
Put all ingredients in electric blender and mix on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is firm. The biscuit mix makes your crust and the coconut is the topping.

title: cinnamon bundt cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients, except nuts together with spoon. Beat with
mixer
until well blended.
Add nuts after mixing. Bake in Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and glaze.

title: mexican-style beans
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.
Drain and cook them, covered, with the diced onions, in about 6 cups of fresh cold water.
Simmer slowly for about 2 hours.
Add butter or bacon drippings and salt.
Simmer one more hour, but remove from heat when they are soft.
More salt may be added, and the bean broth should be thick.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Form in patties.
Fry in oil.
Blend last 5 ingredients together and cook until thickened.
Pour over patties.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Pour 1/4 to 1/2-inch vegetable oil in frypan.
Slice tomatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip slices in flour mixture, then place in hot oil.
Fry for 5 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Garnish with fresh thyme, if desired or sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water, morsels and margarine.
Remove from heat and transfer to large bowl.
Stir in brown sugar; cool 5 minutes. Beat in eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased jelly roll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares. Makes approximately 35 squares.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients with
a
spoon.
Do
not use mixer. Just dump everything in a large bowl; mix and bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a greased pan.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together well.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes a very large pan of brownies.

title: roses cheese cake
directions: Butter inside of pan 8 x 3-inch deep.
Do not use spring-form pan.
Sprinkle crumbs around bottom and sides.
Shake out excess. Beat cheese, eggs, sugar, lemon juice, rind and vanilla on low until blended.
Increase to high.
Continue until thoroughly blended.
Pour into prepared pan; shake to level.
Set pan in slightly larger pan with 1/2-inch of water.
(Not to touch sides.) Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn off oven and let cake stay in oven 20 minutes.
Remove cake from water and place on rack until room temperature.
Invert over plate.
Garnish with fruit if desired.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into small, greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue cocktail hot dogs
directions: Melt butter; add onion and then add all ingredients, but hot dogs.
Bring to a boil, then turn down to low.
Put hot dogs in and simmer 4 hours (hot dogs taste better when they are brown). Put in crock-pot and serve warm with toothpicks.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a small mixing bowl; beat with electric mixer until sugar dissolves.
Continue to beat, slowly adding oil.
Stir in poppy seed.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Stir before serving.
Serve over assorted fresh fruits.
Yield:
1 3/4 cups.

title: white bread
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Scald milk and pour on above.
When lukewarm, add yeast.
Add enough flour until dough is able to be kneaded.
Put dough on floured board and knead, adding flour as necessary.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Put dough into greased bowl.
Rub butter or shortening on top.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size. Punch down; let rise in bowl again until double in size.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook sugar, vinegar and flour.
Add the beets, which have been boiled and peeled, if fresh.
Heat through.

title: yuppie chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in saucepan or microwave.
Pour mixture over cereal.
Use a very large bowl.
Pour mixture into a paper bag and pour a box of powdered sugar over cereal.
Shake bag until all of the cereal is coated.
Pour in doggie bowl and serve. Yields snacks for 5 or 6.

title: mediterranean bean chowder
directions: Combine soup mix, tomatoes, water and beans in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, breaking tomatoes with a spoon.
Add 1/3 cup uncooked macaroni.
Reduce heat to low, partially cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandma's pork cake
directions: *Quakies is what is left after rendering out lard.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large saucepan, cook green pepper and onion in margarine until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add soups, Ro-Tel and chicken, stirring until well blended.
In a 9 x 13 baking dish, alternate layers of tortillas, soup mixture and cheese, repeating 3 layers.
Bake 40 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Whiz all ingredients except cucumber and celery in blender. Then add cucumber and celery.
Chill and serve.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Simmer ground beef, beans and chilies for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: chocolate pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cook on a hot griddle and make small pancakes (no bigger than 3-inches in diameter).

title: coconut caramel cream pie
directions: Filling:
Melt butter in 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Add coconut and pecans.
Saute until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Set aside to cool.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: cherry chew gum
directions: Cream margarine, pecans and flour and press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Set aside to cool.
Soften cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix well and set aside.
Mix Cool Whip into cream cheese.
Spread over cool crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip.
Then spread with cherry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: scallops and mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop.
In large saucepan, melt margarine and stir the stems and scallops for a minute or two. Sprinkle in the flour; stir until it disappears.
Gradually add milk; blend until saucy.
Stir in seasonings and mushroom caps; simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Add celery and pepper; let stand 20 minutes more.
Combine sugar, water, vinegar, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cool and put in freezer containers.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon.
Place mixture in pan.
Then place bacon on top.
Bake 3 hours.
Do not cover.

title: nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and white chocolate together in the microwave or in the top of a double boiler.
Stir in desired amount of nuts.
Cool slightly.
Drop in clusters onto waxed paper.
When set, may be placed in a closed container to store if there's any left by then!

title: yellow summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water until tender; drain.
Add to the sour cream, beaten eggs, carrot, oleo, pepper and soup; mix well.
Put in a 10-inch dish.
Put half stuffing.
Cut cheese in small pieces; put on top.
Dot with oleo.
Put on remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Place sliced apples in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until mixture is thickened.
Pour over apples in dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Roll into walnut sized balls. Freeze on cookie sheets.
After frozen, store in freezer bags. Bake frozen 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° until set, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: brown sugar meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in 2 1/2-quart bowl until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Beat in vanilla.

title: almond cream puffs(serves 6)
directions: In a mixing bowl, whisk together the egg yolks, sugar and cornstarch until light and creamy.
Scald the milk in the top of a double boiler and pour into the egg yolk mixture, whisking constantly to keep the yolks from cooking.
Continue to whisk until the mixture is foamy, then pour into the top of the double boiler.
Cook slowly over simmering water, beating all the while, for about 10 minutes, until it has thickened to the consistency of custard.
Set the double boiler top in a bowl of ice and whisk the custard continuously until it has cooled completely.
Stir in the almond extract, ground almonds and Amaretto.
Whip the cream in a mixing bowl until it forms soft peaks.
Gently fold the custard into the whipped cream until it is thoroughly combined.
Using a pastry bag with a small plain tip, puncture the bottoms of the cream puffs and fill with the custard mixture.
Decorate with sliced strawberries or drizzle with chocolate sauce.
