title: peach embassy(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Wash rice, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Drain at once.
Combine with boiled milk, sugar, salt, butter, orange rind and vanilla extract.
Place in 2-quart ovenproof casserole.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Cover and bake in 325° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is cooked and liquid absorbed.
Remove from oven and remove orange peel.
Cool slightly.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little water.
Add rest of water to sugar and
shortening.
Add salt and add enough flour until it feels velvety.
Put
in
oiled bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk. Punch down.
Let set 10 or 15 minutes and work again.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add coconut and walnuts.
Spread 2/3 of the dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat with the hand to spread evenly.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars and 1 stick butter.
Mix remaining ingredients except frosting in another bowl, alternating between flour and soda mixed into buttermilk.
Add Milky Way mixture.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cake will look moist.
Frost with milk chocolate frosting.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in 1/2-inch slices.
Oil cookie sheet and coat both sides of eggplant with olive oil.
Mix crumbs with seasoning and cheese.
Pile generously on eggplant slices.
Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef,
onions and garlic.	Take off excess fat. Put in
kettle
and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 4 hours (or
longer).
One
hour before serving time, add 1 small can of mushrooms.
This
sauce
and 1 pound of spaghetti serves 4 to 6.

title: nen naw's karo nut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add Karo and pecans. Pour in uncooked pie shell and bake for about one hour in a 350° oven.

title: black-eyed pea fritters
directions: Drain the black-eyed peas and mash with potato masher. Combine all other ingredients; stir well and drop by full teaspoons in hot oil in skillet.
Brown well.

title: moist brownies
directions: Melt the oleo in pan.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl and pour the melted oleo in the bowl with the other ingredients.
Mix well and pour in your pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Check them at 25 minutes; do not overbake.

title: pan release
directions: Mix all ingredients well in an electric mixer until smooth. Works well.

title: hearty cheese soup
directions: Saute celery, carrots and onion in butter slowly until soft. Mix flour and cornstarch into vegetables.
Add broth, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir over medium heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and add soda and cheese.
Serve with parsley sprinkled on top.
Freezes well.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and set aside 1/4 cup juice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Dissolve marshmallows in jello and add remaining juice.

title: it's a snap cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, mix unflavored gelatine with sugar. Add boiling water and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved. With electric mixer, beat in cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Make sure there are no lumps.
Pour into prepared crust. Chill until firm.
When firm, top with your favorite pie filling.

title: easy torte
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in crackers, chopped nuts, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake in greased 9-inch pie pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream and shaved sweet chocolate or vanilla ice cream and chocolate syrup.

title: rich and creamy chicken
directions: Wrap bacon around each breast.
Place layer of dried beef in bottom of baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top.
Mix soup, sour cream and cream cheese; spread over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Remove foil and brown for a few minutes.
Serve with white rice.
Serves 12.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and set aside.
In large bowl, beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Blend in pineapple with liquid, carrots, coconut and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Place chicken in large pan.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and add tomatoes, garlic, onion and chilies.
Slide chicken meat off bones and return meat to broth.
Add beans and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with tortillas.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Mix together the following: salad oil, vinegar, water, lemon juice, oregano, garlic powder, salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 tomato, cut up, just before serving.

title: scallops in cheese sauce
directions: Place scallops, wine and parsley in 3-quart saucepan. Add water to cover. Heat to boiling and cook, uncovered, 8 minutes. Remove scallops, reserving liquid. Reduce liquid to 1 cup by boiling; strain and reserve. Cook mushrooms and onions in butter approximately 5 to 6 minutes and remove from pan.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour and stir over low heat until smooth and bubbly. Stir in reserved liquid, half and half, scallops, onions and mushrooms and 1/4 cup cheese.
Heat until hot.
Toss bread crumbs in butter separately. Grease baking dishes and divide scallop mixture among them.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and top with bread crumbs. Broil 3 to 5-inches from broiler, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine spices and tie in cheesecloth.
Place in apple cider and brown sugar mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes or until spicy as desired.
Remove bag and serve in mugs with grated nutmeg or cinnamon stick in each.

title: mushroom sauce(serve with steaks or on hamburgers)
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms. Thicken with flour and water.

title: homemade eagle brand milk
directions: Mix nonfat dry milk and warm water.
Stir in 3/4 cup sugar, stirring to dissolve sugar.
This equals 1 can.

title: pizza snack
directions: Brown ground beef, add salt & pepper if desired; drain. Place on paper towels to absorb excess grease. On cookie sheet or pizza pan flatten biscuits with rolling pin. Spread pizza sauce and beef, top with cheese and other toppings if desired. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Sprinkle soda over pulp.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs. Combine ingredients.
For bars use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and let stand for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Stew seasoned chicken until tender.
Cool and remove from bone. Cut in small pieces.
Thicken broth chicken was stewed in with cornstarch.
Add bean sprouts (drained), chow mein vegetables (drained), soy sauce, and then add cut up chicken.
Cook rice as you normally would.
Serve chow mein and Chinese noodles on your rice.
Sprinkle generously with soy sauce.

title: sweet 'n' sour wings
directions: Brown chicken wings well in non-stick frying pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over browned wings.
Cook over medium-low heat until the sauce coats the chicken and sticks to it, about 20-30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and eggs together.
Add cocoa to egg mixture and blend well.
Add sour milk or buttermilk to cocoa mixture and blend well.
Add sifted flour mixture to cocoa mixture and blend well.
Add hot water to cocoa mixture and blend well. Pour cake batter into 2 (9-inch) round pans or 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan and bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° about 1 hour.
Makes a 10-inch pie.

title: barbecues
directions: Mix together, put in crock-pot and serve on buns.

title: pickled fish
directions: Cut salmon into bite size pieces.
Rinse well and let stand overnight in container of cold water.
Drain.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook noodles.
Drain tuna fish. Separate tuna with fork.
Grease ovenproof pan (10 x 15 x 2-inch). Arrange layer of noodles, tuna, cheese and so on until noodles on top.
Pour soup and sherry mixture over noodles.
Cover.
Top with corn flakes or crumbs.

title: a special salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a quart jar; mix. Shake vigorously. Store in refrigerator.

title: cheddar potatoes
directions: Crush corn flakes and combine with 1/2 stick melted margarine; set aside. Mix the rest of the ingredients in a large bowl. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8 x 8-inch pans.
Spread in potato mixture. Sprinkle corn flake mixture over potatoes.
Shake on paprika for color, if desired.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Sieve together all dry ingredients; add eggs.
Mix in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Let stand 1 hour.
Pour into crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°; cut down heat to 325° and bake 40 minutes more.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix well all dry ingredients.
Add oil or lard; mix well. Slowly add water into mixture.
Knead well.
Make into small balls.
Roll out thin and brown on pancake grill.
Wrap in cloth or plastic bag to keep them from getting hard.
Makes about 15.

title: cowboy's caviar
directions: First Layer:
Mix jalapeno dip and taco seasoning.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add vinegar, vanilla and cold water. Mix well.
Add liquid shortening.
Mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Combine drained fruits and set aside.
In small bowl, combine pudding mix, milk and orange juice concentrate.
Beat with mixer until blended.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture and chill.
Serves 10.

title: chicken jerusalem
directions: Roll each chicken breast in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Brown in 125 grams butter until golden brown.
Add all of the ingredients in a 2-quart frypan.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender.
Then stir in 2 cups of heavily warmed whipping cream to chicken and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve.
Sprinkle with freshly cut parsley.
Serve with wild rice or saffron rice with green spinach salad, croutons and Blue cheese dressing.

title: baked corn a la southern
directions: Mix corn, slightly beaten egg, salt, pepper, melted butter and milk together.
Place in buttered baking dish; cover with cracker crumbs and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a slow oven about 1/2 hour or until firm.
Serve hot.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Soak poppy seed in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Combine cake mix, pudding, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add poppy seed and water mixture; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: all star chili
directions: Brown beef, chicken and pork chops in oil in a wok or large skillet and set aside. Grill sausage links on barbecue; cut into bite-size pieces and set aside. Combine browned meat and sausage in a very large pot. Lightly brown onion in olive oil in wok. Add onion, cilantro and remaining vegetables to meats. Add canned beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste and next 11 spices to pot. Add liquid ingredients, peanut butter and brown sugar to pot and stir mixture well. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stir well. Reduce heat and simmer for 12 hour on low heat, stir occasionally. Turn off heat; let cool and remove excess grease from top. Reheat to serve. Serve with cheddar cheese, sour cream and diced Vidalia onions. Serve with garlic or hard bread and Merlot wine. Makes 6 quarts.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
No need to thaw potatoes completely, just enough to get them apart, especially if you're not going to cook immediately.
Mix together potatoes, 1/4 cup butter, salt, pepper, sour cream, onion, milk, cheese, and cream of celery soup. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed cornflakes, mixed with 1/4 cup butter.
Bake for 45 minutes.
This is good to make ahead, freezes well.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Layer Club crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil the next 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate bits.
Pour this over the second layer of crackers.
Chill and cut into small squares.

title: walnut drop cookies
directions: Crush cereal slightly.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In mixing bowl, beat oleo and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in cereal and nuts.

title: garden stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425.
Microwave pierced potatoes on HIGH for 12 minutes; bake for 15 minutes.
Slice off potato tops.
Scoop out pulp, keeping skins intact.
Mash pulp in a medium bowl.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine the blackberries, 1 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and lemon extract.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, nutmeg and remaining sugar and salt.
Add milk; stir just until mixed.
(Dough will be very thick.)
Drop by tablespoonfuls into six mounds onto hot blackberry mixture; cover tightly and simmer for 15 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in a dumpling comes out clean.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Serve with cream or whipped cream if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: bayrun's breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Add sausage.
Mix eggs, 2 1/2 cups
milk and dry mustard.
Sprinkle on mushrooms and cheese.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all this.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: orange-coconut cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use 4 pans.
Cool cake layers.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan over low fire.
Add rice, soups and milk; combine.
Lay chicken over rice and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours. Leave covered entire baking time.

title: jalapeno hominy
directions: Combine all ingredients together and put in a baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or microwave for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Half the zucchini lengthwise.
Scoop out zucchini halves leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Rinse and drain.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet until beef is light brown. Drain.
Stir in rice, salt, garlic salt, chili powder and 1 cup of tomato sauce.
Heat through.
Stuff each zucchini half with beef mixture.
Place in an ungreased baking pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over the zucchini.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Refrigerate overnight for full flavor.

title: potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes and prick with a fork. Bake in a 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until tender. Cool. Cut each potato lengthwise into 4 wedges. Scoop out the inside of each potato wedge. Cover and chill the leftover fluffy white part of potatoes for another use. In a small bowl, combine the oil, chili powder, and hot pepper sauce. Using a pastry brush, brush the inside of potatoes with the oil mixture. Place the potato wedges in a single layer on a large baking sheet. Sprinkle wedges with bacon, tomato, and green onion, top with cheese. Bake about 10 minutes or until cheese melts and potatoes are heated through. If desired, serve with sour cream. Makes 24 wedges.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together for dressing.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool firm before serving.

title: apple salad
directions: Chop celery; cut apples.
Mix all ingredients; serve at once. Makes about 6 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: ham and cabbage dinner
directions: Place ham, onion, celery and garlic in soup pot (large!) with bay leaf and 6 to 8 cups water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Take ham out. Add potatoes and carrots and return to medium-high heat for 1/2 hour or until veggies are done.
Add cabbage and cook at medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Either slice ham and return to pot, or keep ham warm on platter and serve with vegetables on the side.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple (juice included) until almost boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin until it is dissolved.
Allow pineapple gelatin mixture to cool completely before adding buttermilk and whipped topping.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 3/4-quart casserole dish and sprinkle top with chopped pecans.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and butter to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and corn flakes; stir well.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and pour melted chocolate over top. Refrigerate, if desired.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until done, take off the bone and chop.
Cool and add the salt and pepper, salad cubes, onion and celery.
Mix with mayonnaise and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, butter and cream cheese.
Add oil, sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and almond extract; mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: pecan patties
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients to a soft ball stage, using a candy thermometer. Add nuts and let mixture regain heat.
(It's best to use a heavy pan; this doesn't take long to cook.)
Remove from heat when it comes back to a full boil
with nuts in it.
Add butter, vanilla and red coloring.
Beat with spoon until mixture looks creamy and thickens.
Drop or pour into buttered pan or muffin tins.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Layer
all ingredients in dish in order listed.
Sprinkle top with Town House crackers, crumbled.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve piping hot!

title: never fail frosting
directions: Put sugar, egg whites, 1 teaspoon vanilla and other ingredients in top of double boiler.
Beat until stiff.
Enough to frost 2 layer cakes.
Good for Coconut Cake.

title: pasta plaza
directions: Cube tomatoes approximately 1 inch, spread evenly in large casserole.
Cut butter or margarine into pats and lay on top of tomatoes.
Sprinkle garlic salt and oregano to taste.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese generously over casserole.
Place casserole under broiler.
Stir frequently, cook until tomatoes are well softened and Parmesan cheese is slightly toasted.
Serve over pasta.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
In a 9 x 12-inch casserole, layer small pieces of broccoli on bottom, then layer chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon together.
Pour over top.
Next layer cheese, then bread stuffing.
Pour melted butter over stuffing.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chinese chews cookies
directions: Mix and sift cake flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add nuts, dates, eggs and vanilla.
Put in greased shallow cake pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While hot, roll teaspoonfuls into balls in powdered sugar or granulated sugar.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix.
Pour sauce over roast and cover.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours. Remove meat.
Shred with a fork and return to sauce.
Mix and heat through.
Serve on buns.

title: orange glazed pork loin
directions: Use a roast tied with string instead of a stocking.
Roast is best if seasoned the day before.
Sauce can be made the day before too.
Preheat the oven to 325 degrees.
Combine the salt, thyme, ginger, and pepper in small bowl.
With sharp knife, make slits in roast and insert a slice of garlic and some of the spice mixture into each.
Rub the roast with remaining spice mixture.
Insert meat thermometer.
Place roast, uncovered, in a roasting pan and bake for a total of 3 hours.
Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, combine the flour, cornstarch, and sugar.
Add orange juice gradually, then the remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat and whisk about 3 to 5 minutes, until smooth and thick.
After the pork has roasted for 2 hours, brush the roast frequently with the glaze. (I put a little sauce in a separate bowl to use as glaze so the meat won't contaminate the rest of the sauce.)
Continue roasting and basting for another hour, or until the meat thermometer registers 170 degrees.
Heat remaining glaze and serve as a sauce with the sliced pork.
Makes 10 servings.

title: crescents
directions: Soften oleo.
Sift flour and salt together.
Mix oleo, sugar, milk and vanilla together until creamy.
Add flour and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Take a teaspoon of dough; roll into a small ball. Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: mocked whipped topping
directions: Cook 1 cup milk with 2 tablespoons flour until thick and clear.
Cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Then pour over the other ingredients; toss well.
If you want to double recipe, you can add 2 heads of broccoli and double mayonnaise mixture.

title: swiss cheese chicken bake
directions: Lay chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Lay Swiss cheese over chicken pieces.
Mix cream of chicken soup and 1/2 cup white wine.
Pour over cheese and chicken.
Crumble Pepperidge Farm stuffing over whole casserole.
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Saute onion in small amount of fat until tender.
Combine Bisquick, 3/4 cup cheese, parsley and onion.
Add milk and egg. Spoon into 8 x 8-inch square or 8-inch round pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, and drizzle margarine over.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: suisse mocha
directions: Place ingredients in a blender and process until the consistency of powder is reached, or sift ingredients together several times.
To prepare 1 serving, place 2 rounded teaspoons in a cup.
Add 6 to 8 ounces of boiling water.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix above together (will be very thick).
Divide into 3 round 9-inch pans.
Bake 350° until done.
Let cool before frosting. Put frosting on thick between layers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and combine with graham cracker crumbs. Pat mixture firmly in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine eggs, remaining margarine and powdered sugar and beat mixture for no less than 15 minutes.
Add crushed and drained pineapple.
Spread mixture evenly over graham cracker mixture and cover with sliced bananas (brush with lemon juice to prevent darkening).
Next, smooth on Cool Whip to cover mixture completely.
Garnish with nuts and sliced cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: pudding chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, pudding mix and vanilla until smooth. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour and soda.
Stir in chips.
Drop from spoon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: red cabbage and apple slaw
directions: If you have a food processor with a julienne blade, this is an excellent opportunity to use it.
If not, slice the carrots as thinly as possible with a vegetable peeler, then with a sharp knife, cut slices into thread-like strips.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in plastic bag.
Drop in beef and shake until coated.
Mix with 2 tablespoons oil in 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes, stirring once.
Add vegetables, water and tomato sauce.
Mix well. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours or until done.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: old fashion cutout cookies
directions: Cream sugar, lard and butter.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and almond.
Mix in remaining ingredients and blend well.
Chill overnight.
Roll out dough and cut into shapes.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into balls.
Place fork in sugar and make a crisscross pattern on the cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate mocha mousse
directions: Combine sugar, water and coffee; boil 3 minutes.
Using metal blade of food processor, add cream and mix until very thick, about 1 minute.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Place blade back; don't rinse bowl.
Add chocolate chips and process on/off for 20 seconds.
Continue processing. Add hot syrup, Kahlua and egg yolks.
Process 20 seconds approximately.
Fold whipped cream into chocolate mixture.
Freeze or chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: people chow
directions: Mix peanut butter and chocolate chips in a large pan over low heat, stirring constantly, until creamy and smooth.
Add cereal. Put sugar into a paper bag.
Dump cereal mixture into bag and shake until coated.
Turn onto cookie sheet and cool.

title: french breakfast muffins
directions: Heat
oven
Grease 15 muffin cups. Mix thoroughly shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and the egg.
Stir in flour, baking powder,
salt
and nutmeg alternately with milk.
Fill muffin cups
full.
Bake
20 to 25 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar
and the cinnamon.
Immediately after baking, roll puffs in melted butter, then in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Serve hot.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix baking powder with graham cracker crumbs.
Add alternately with milk and pineapple to creamed mixture; add vanilla.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Bake in a tube or Bundt pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: condensed milk
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop from tablespoon.
Dip fork in cold water to shape cookies.
Place about 2 inches apart. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Prepare bottom pie crust in pie dish.
Fry hamburg; drain when done.
Add creamed corn; mix well.
On bottom layer of pie, add 1 layer of Mozzarella cheese, then pour hamburg and corn mixture over cheese.
Now, add remaining cheese to the top of mixture and place top pie crust on.
Crimp pie crust edges together.
Poke holes in top.
Bake in a 425° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy turkey salad
directions: In large bowl stir together soup and mayonnaise until smooth. Fold in turkey, celery, red pepper, onions, parsley and pepper. Cover and refrigerate. Makes about 5 cups.

title: cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix butter, cheese and mustard together and spread on frozen bread.
Cut slices into thirds.
Bake at 100° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and pepper together.
Add egg, milk and margarine.
Stir to moisten.
Stir in corn.
Add oil to large skillet.
Heat oil to medium hot.
Drop corn mixture by tablespoonful into hot skillet.
Turn each corn fritter over when it is golden brown.
Fry until second side is golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Top with maple syrup, if desired and serve.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes and onion like potato soup.
Drain vegetables. In small bowl, blend flour with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour 2 cups milk over vegetables.
Add flour, milk and clams.
Cook, stirring until it thickens.
Do not let boil.
Add seasoning and cooked bacon pieces.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and egg.
Add mashed bananas.
Next, mix flour with soda, sifted.
Add vanilla.
Fold in fruit and nuts which have been floured.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: olive-nut sandwich spread
directions: Put all ingredients into small bowl; blend well.
Refrigerate unused portion.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip; fold in sliced bananas.
Line dish with wafers.
Top with 1/2 of mixture.
Repeat layers and top with Cool Whip.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk; add eggs (slightly beaten), sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla extract and raisins.
Stir thoroughly. Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until firm and lightly brown.
Cool thoroughly and cut into squares.

title: stir-fry rice
directions: In large, heated skillet, pour safflower oil and add rice. Mix angel hair with rice; stir until golden brown.
Add water and sauce mix.
Stir.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in all other ingredients and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat; add beef broth, gravy mix and vegetables.
Stir; simmer about 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Place mixture in casserole; top with Bisquick biscuits and bake at 450° for about 15 minutes.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Grate cheese and put 1/2 of it on the bottom of a 7 x 7-inch pan.
Then beat eggs and taco sauce together.
Pour over cheese and add the rest of the cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with taco chips.

title: nanna's and mommy's hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat in a Dutch oven.
Add chopped onion and brown in meat drippings.
(If there's too much fat, remove some before adding onion.)
Add grated carrot and potato, beef bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring just to the boil, then reduce heat to a simmer, cover and cook about 40 minutes.
(Check periodically. If not much liquid remains, add water or more bouillon.)
Serve with baking powder biscuits.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together shortening, sugars, vanilla and egg.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Then stir in chips.
Drop from a teaspoon 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then move to rack to finish cooling.
Makes approximately 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in cold water.
Cream shortening and sugar. Beat in egg.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water and beat.
Sift dry ingredients together, then fold into liquids.
Place dough in refrigerator
covered for 4 hours or longer.
Allow 2 hours to rise at room temperature.
After rising, flour hands and shape into rolls.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Makes approximately 35 small rolls.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except 1/2 cup crumbs and put in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: taco shells
directions: *Do not use self-rising flour in this recipe.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Combine 1/3 cup soup with ground beef.
Add breadcrumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into six oval patties in a frying pan. Brown patties.
Drain off fat.
Blend flour in remaining soup; mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Add to frypan.
Heat to boil.
Stir to loosen up.
Cover for 5 minutes on low heat.
Then add patties to gravy in same pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, until meat is done.
Serves 6. Also easy to freeze for fast heat up meals.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into jelly roll pan, that has been lined with waxed paper and lightly greased.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Immediately flip onto a damp dish towel; roll up and cool.
Unroll and spread with the filling.

title: cheese baguettes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on sliced bread.
Bake in oven until cheese melts and serve.

title: frito salad
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Add beans, taco sauce, taco seasoning; set aside.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes and onion in large mixing bowl.
At last minute before serving, mix all ingredients together including cheese and Fritos.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Heat milk just to boiling point. Pour over cocoa mix, stirring with wire whip until well mixed. Add vanilla.
Serve at once.
Makes 12 servings.

title: baglava
directions: Thoroughly mix together almond, cardamon and powdered sugar. Set aside.
In a flat baking pan combine egg yolks, milk and melted butter.
Add flour little by little, until a dough is formed.
The dough should not stick to your hand.
Divide the dough into 5 equal portions and place each portion into a plastic bag.
Remove dough one piece at a time and make five sheets to fit the size of the pan.
Cover the bottom of a well-greased pan with 2 pastry sheets. Brush each sheet with melted butter before placing the next sheet on top.
Place 2 more sheets on top, grease each sheet.
Cut pastry into 1 x 1-inch squares.
Add 3 or 4 tablespoons melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden. Immediately drizzle syrup on top.
Cover the pan with aluminum foil and let cool.
Sprinkle pistachios on top just prior to serving.

title: gene's finger pizza rolls
directions: Grind meat, cheese and pepper together; add seasoning and tomato paste. Mix well; set aside.
Remove crust from bread; roll each individual slice very thin.

Spread each slice with meat mixture and roll like small jelly roll using toothpick to hold together if needed; brush with melted butter and bake on greased cookie sheets at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream fudge cake
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening, add sour cream and eggs; beat well.
Add chocolate and hot water.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, beat well.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350°.
If using 9 x 13-inch pan bake 35 minutes. If using 9-inch layer pans bake 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Favorite Fudge Frosting.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix in peanut butter. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.

title: banana salad cups
directions: Mix everything together, except cherries.
Freeze in cupcake cups.
Garnish with a drained cherry.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350°.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Saute chillies and onion.
Add other ingredients and put into large baking dish.
Top with 1 to 2 cups grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with sour cream and olives.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook meat with onion, green pepper, celery and season to taste; drain well.
Mix spaghetti with butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Mix meat with spaghetti sauce.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix mandarin oranges, Cool Whip, fruit cocktail, pineapple, vanilla instant pudding and lemon instant pudding.
Put in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: hello dollie cookies
directions: Melt oleo in Pyrex dish; pour butter into bowl and add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour back into dish you used to melt butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Pour rice, water and soups over top.
Salt and pepper. Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: baked livers
directions: Take first 3 ingredients and marinate overnight.
After they have marinated, place on paper towel to absorb excess.
Take a liver and wrap in a piece of bacon; secure with toothpick.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Before placing on cookie sheet, roll livers in brown sugar.

title: friendship cake
directions: In a gallon glass or plastic jug, pour starter juice.
Add 2 1/2 cups sugar and peaches.
Stir every 10 days with a wooden spoon.

title: sugar-free spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water until moist.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and cocoa.
Set aside.
Add to raisins, vanilla, eggs, oil, Sweet 'N Low and applesauce.
Add to flour mixture.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marinaded grilled vegetables
directions: In a small bowl, combine marinade ingredients.
Cut vegetables into pieces appropriate for skewering.
Place vegetables in a large bowl.
Pour marinade over and toss to coat well.
Marinate up to 2 hours.
Reserve marinade.
Place vegetables on skewers (on type of vegetable per skewers).
Cook vegetables over medium grill for 7 to 15 minutes, turning and basting with remaining marinade frequently until fork-tender.
When cooked, push vegetables off skewers into serving dish and toss gently.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and sugar.
Drizzle melted butter into the mixture to moisten.
Using your fingertips, press the graham cracker mixture into the bottom of a 10-inch round spring-form pan.
Place the pan in the refrigerator for 15 minutes or until crust is firm to the touch.

title: glazed walnuts(a thin crackly candy coats the nuts.)
directions: Combine sugar and water in a small heavy saucepan.

Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves, then cook rapidly, without stirring, to 300° on a candy thermometer, or until a spoonful of syrup poured into a cup of cold water forms hard brittle threads that break when pressed.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in baking pan.
Pour cake mix over; top with pecans and dot with the oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate onions, fine or
drop in food processor or blender.
At room
temperature,
combine
1st three ingredients and form one large ball or two smaller ones.
Roll in chopped nuts or paprika to cover.

title: bearnaise sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine vinegar, wine, shallots and tarragon. Bring to a boil and cook until reduced by half (3 to 4 tablespoons).
Place egg yolks and butter in top half of double boiler over hot water and beat until thick.
Strain vinegar mixture into egg mixture.
Gradually add melted butter, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add seasonings.
Serve over beef or other grilled meats.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: *Peaches, apricots, pineapple chunks, pears, mandarin oranges or equivalents; for ham use only pineapple chunks and maraschino cherries.

title: german chocolate pan cake(microwave)
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 1/4-inch cake pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and coconut in bottom of
pan.

title: roasted tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes.
Cut in halves and scoop out seeds. Lay tomatoes in shallow pan, coated with Mazola oil.
Crumble bread in bowl.
Add parsley, basil, remaining oil, garlic salt, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Mix very lightly.
Place ingredients on each half tomato.
Bake in 375° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mary's meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients with hands.
Add ketchup as needed while mixing.
When mixed well, form into a loaf and put into pan.
Cover with foil. Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake until brown. Remove from grease.
Serve warm.

title: spinach salad
directions: Place in a jar and shake.

title: cherry pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in sugar; add flour.
Stir until a ball forms.
Spread into a pie plate with spoon or fingers on bottom and up the sides.
Pour 1 can cherry pie filling over crust.
Add topping and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Do not preheat oven.
